p-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-96\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"housing-rennovation-icon\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a> Housing and Renovation</h2>\r\nWe have collected over half a million HIPPOBAGs from residential properties, so we understand the challenges of waste disposal in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods.\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a> Retail and Office Fitout</h2>\r\nDuring the refurbishment or fit out stage of retail and office premises, using a HIPPOBAG allows you to segregate waste streams on site, helping you to achieve increased recycling rates. This in return helps you to achieve your diversion from landfill objectives.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPOWASTE you’ll also benefit from the flexibility of an instant and non-bulky waste solution that is transportable and bespoke to your project. HIPPOWASTE work around your business, with our flat packed bags able to be used at any time – up to a year –after purchase, and being collected at a time of your convenience. This way you no-longer have to wait for skip deliveries or collections that clutter sites, hampering the progress of your workforce.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /> Plasterboard Recycling</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE also offer a quick and cost effective way of getting rid of plasterboard from your site or property. Through our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect. HIPPO’s environmental values mean that you can ensure that you are disposing of your waste in a responsible and eco-friendly manner.\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-97\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"installation-icon\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a> Installations</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE offers an ideal service for installations. We understand the importance of minimising disruption and inconvenience to customers and their surrounding properties during a domestic remodelling. HIPPOBAGs ensure that waste is kept neatly and takes up as little room as possible.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so don’t waste room before they are used. In addition, our reliable and flexible courier service means that you can arrange for your HIPPOBAG to be picked up at a convenient time for you. HIPPOBAGS can also be left on your – or your customer’s – property, making them far more tidy and convenient than a traditional skip that would be left on the road.\r\n\r\nFor bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG is ideal, able to hold an entire bathroom suite. The larger 4.5 Yard HIPPOSKIP was developed to accommodate kitchen and larger bathroom installation projects.','Services','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 10:39:46','2015-03-11 10:39:46','',6,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=106',0,'revision','',0),(108,2,'2015-03-11 10:43:18','2015-03-11 10:43:18','<h1>About Us</h1>\r\n<h2>Why Choose HIPPO?</h2>\r\nSelecting a waste logistics service is a vital decision for any business. HIPPOWASTE provide a reliable, affordable and convenient national skip alternative for any sized business. Our innovative HIPPOBAG comes in three convenient sizes and is available either online or from our trusted stockists around the UK.\r\n\r\nA HIPPOBAG is the perfect alternative to traditional skip hire for a number of reasons; a HIPPOBAG is bought flat packed and can be used at a convenient time for you, where you would have a limited time if you hired a skip. When you are finished with your HIPPOBAG, simply arrange a collection and our professional couriers will collect your waste and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs also take up very little space and you can suit the size of bag to the size of your project, this means you don’t need to pay the full price that you would for a skip if your needs are smaller.\r\n\r\nHIPPO’s environmental policies mean that you can be reassured that your waste is being handled and disposed of in a responsible manner. We typically recycle around 90% of the waste that we collect. HIPPO are also committed to excellent customer service and have an excellent average customer review rating of 4.7 out of 5.\r\n<h2>Our Waste Logistics Experts</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE provide waste logistics services for a great number of projects. Whether you require waste management in projects such as as new build and construction, housing and renovation, facilities management, kitchen and bathroom installation, retail and office fit out or virtually any project where waste is produced. HIPPOWASTE also run a dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, where we collect uncontaminated plasterboard and recycle 100% of it.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO’s trusted, project–specific approach we can suit our service perfectly to your waste logistics needs, whilst ensuring that you receive value for money and that your waste is dealt with responsibly.','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','33-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 10:43:18','2015-03-11 10:43:18','',33,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=108',0,'revision','',0),(110,2,'2015-03-11 10:44:58','2015-03-11 10:44:58','<h1>Careers</h1>\r\n\r\nThe chances are, when you join us, you’ve got more than a job in mind. You’ll be thinking about how joining HIPPO will contribute to your longer term aims – and so will we.\r\nWe work to provide opportunities for development through both training and through career development. Our training is themed around individuals’ career objectives, departmental requirements, and wider business needs or changes, making sure we’re all ready for our next challenge.\r\nWe are particularly proud of our team’s career progression – we’re not a huge organisation, but through creative thinking, an eye for talent, and the flexibility that comes with the Company’s growth and development, we have been able to spot opportunities for people to move to roles which are more senior, more challenging, or represent a change of career. This is great for us, as we retain our committed and talented people; and it allows people with talent and ambition to pursue their career aspirations. 9% of our team were promoted into their current roles, and 12% have moved to a different role during their time with HIPPO.\r\n\r\nTo apply for any of these roles, please email your CV with a covering letter to recruitment@hippowaste.co.uk. Alternatively you can upload your CV online to send it through to us or post it to: HR Department, HIPPO, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth PO6 3EN','Careers at HIPPOWASTE','','inherit','open','open','','34-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 10:44:58','2015-03-11 10:44:58','',34,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=110',0,'revision','',0),(112,2,'2015-03-11 10:47:04','2015-03-11 10:47:04','<h1>Careers</h1>\r\nThe chances are, when you join us, you’ve got more than a job in mind. You’ll be thinking about how joining HIPPO will contribute to your longer term aims – and so will we.\r\n\r\nWe work to provide opportunities for development through both training and through career development. Our training is themed around individuals’ career objectives, departmental requirements, and wider business needs or changes, making sure we’re all ready for our next challenge.\r\nWe are particularly proud of our team’s career progression – we’re not a huge organisation, but through creative thinking, an eye for talent, and the flexibility that comes with the Company’s growth and development, we have been able to spot opportunities for people to move to roles which are more senior, more challenging, or represent a change of career. This is great for us, as we retain our committed and talented people; and it allows people with talent and ambition to pursue their career aspirations. 9% of our team were promoted into their current roles, and 12% have moved to a different role during their time with HIPPO.\r\n\r\nTo apply for any of vacancies, please email your CV with a covering letter to recruitment@hippowaste.co.uk or post it to: HR Department, HIPPO, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth PO6 3EN\r\n<h2>Current Vacancies</h2>\r\nWe have no current vacancies.','Careers at HIPPOWASTE','','inherit','open','open','','34-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 10:47:04','2015-03-11 10:47:04','',34,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=112',0,'revision','',0),(119,2,'2015-03-11 11:31:01','2015-03-11 11:31:01','<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"housing-rennovation-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>\r\n<h1>Housing and Renovation</h1>','Housing and Renovation','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 11:31:01','2015-03-11 11:31:01','',11,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=119',0,'revision','',0),(120,2,'2015-03-11 11:31:41','2015-03-11 11:31:41','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"housing-rennovation-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Housing and Renovation</h1>','Housing and Renovation','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 11:31:41','2015-03-11 11:31:41','',11,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=120',0,'revision','',0),(122,2,'2015-03-11 11:32:22','2015-03-11 11:32:22','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-97\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"installation-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Installations</h1>','Installation','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 11:32:22','2015-03-11 11:32:22','',12,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=122',0,'revision','',0),(124,2,'2015-03-11 11:32:57','2015-03-11 11:32:57','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Retail and Office Fitout</h1>','Retail and Offices Fitout','','inherit','open','open','','13-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 11:32:57','2015-03-11 11:32:57','',13,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=124',0,'revision','',0),(126,2,'2015-03-11 11:33:26','2015-03-11 11:33:26','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities-management-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-95\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities-management-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"facilities-management-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Facilities Management</h1>','Facilities Management','','inherit','open','open','','14-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 11:33:26','2015-03-11 11:33:26','',14,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=126',0,'revision','',0),(528,2,'2015-06-01 11:18:18','2015-06-01 10:18:18','<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Plasterboard-Service-Image.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-493\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Plasterboard-Service-Image.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"549\" /></a>HIPPO Provides Waste Logistics Services for Recycling Plasterboard</h2>\n&nbsp;\n\nHIPPOWASTE can provide a quick and reliable service to allow you to remove excess plasterboard from your site. As part of our commitment to responsible and ethical waste logistics, our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme means that we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect.\n<h2>Segregation</h2>\nIn addition to collecting plasterboard, HIPPO\'s reliable, flexible and convenient service allows the segregation of different types of waste from your project. This means that you can easily increase your company’s recycling rates, as well as saving money on landfill tax.\n<h2>recycling</h2>\nHIPPO recycles around 90 per cent of waste that we collect, so provide a responsible method of removing general waste from your project. We also offer reviews of environmental performance on a site by site basis – including a breakdown by waste stream and percentage of landfill diversion.\n<h2>national service</h2>\nWe offer a national waste logistics service, meaning that both regional and national operations are ideally suited to HIPPO.\n\nHIPPOBAGs are non-bulky and lightweight, meaning that space can be saved on-site whilst you are undertaking your project. In addition to being an affordable price, strong, convenient HIPPOBAGs come in three different sizes, so you can suit the size of HIPPOBAG used for your specific project and save money.\n\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/plasterboard-recycling-case-study/\">Read our Plasterboard Recycling case study here.</a>','Plasterboard Recycling','','inherit','open','open','','15-autosave-v1','','','2015-06-01 11:18:18','2015-06-01 10:18:18','',15,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/15-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(128,2,'2015-03-11 11:34:02','2015-03-11 11:34:02','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Plasterboard Recycling</h1>','Plasterboard Recycling','','inherit','open','open','','15-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 11:34:02','2015-03-11 11:34:02','',15,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=128',0,'revision','',0),(129,2,'2015-03-11 11:35:33','2015-03-11 11:35:33','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Construction</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHIPPO provides waste management services to projects across the construction sector, including social housing, retail and internal fit-out.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The flexibility of the HIPPOBAG’s allows for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites</li>\r\n	<li>National service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are</li>\r\n	<li>Not just bags, if you need something bigger we can support you with wheelie bins, skips and Ro-Ro’s as required</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>From start to finish</h2>\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n\r\nWhy do construction sites across the UK use HIPPO?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Flexibility in the location of the bag helps to reduce double handling. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, to improve site efficiency.</li>\r\n	<li>One supplier for all your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a title=\"Plasterboard Recycling\" href=\"http://www.hippowaste.co.uk/case-studies/plasterboard-recycling\" rel=\"nofollow\">plasterboard</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>Different bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and improve diversion from landfill.</li>\r\n	<li>Bespoke solutions developed for each site to give you flexibility in collection volumes and timing.</li>\r\n</ul>','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 11:35:33','2015-03-11 11:35:33','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=129',0,'revision','',0),(130,2,'2015-03-11 11:37:10','2015-03-11 11:37:10','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"housing-rennovation-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Housing and Renovation</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEnsuring that existing housing supply across the country is well-maintained and meets a minimum standard of decency is fundamental to healthy and happy communities. HIPPO™ is ideally placed to support refurbishment projects in this vital field. We have a thorough grasp of your challenges in disposing of the waste generated in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods – compounded by operating to strict deadlines and within tight budgets.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Nationwide network for rapid collection.</li>\r\n	<li>3 bag sizes means you have the perfect bag for the job.</li>\r\n	<li>Flat packed bags – no waiting for a skip.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHIPPO has collected over 500,000 bags from domestic properties since 2005. With this level of experience you can be sure of a safe and hassle free collection from the customer’s property. We can also help you to maintain your reputation as a good corporate citizen and fulfil your duty of care to the communities in which you work, by minimising the social and environmental impact of your operations.\r\n\r\nAs well as reducing the direct costs of waste management, we can improve operational efficiencies and minimise disruption and distractions to your core activities. A typical decent homes project produces 2-5 cubic yards of waste from kitchen units, bathroom suites, and central heating systems. HIPPOBAGs, from the 1 cubic yard MIDIBAG to the 4.5 yard MIGHTYBAG, are ideal for the disposal of these waste streams. MEGABAGs were designed to hold a bathroom suite and a single MIGHTYBAG has capacity for both a bathroom suite AND a medium kitchen.','Housing and Renovation','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 11:37:10','2015-03-11 11:37:10','',11,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=130',0,'revision','',0),(250,2,'2015-03-12 10:46:12','2015-03-12 10:46:12','The MIGHTYBAG (aka the HIPPOSKIP<sup>TM</sup>) was designed with kitchen and large bathroom installations in mind. The 4.5 cubic yard bag is ideal for light, bulky waste, and can easily accommodate the waste created by a standard kitchen installation. In fact, our customers find that 78% of all kitchen installations fit into a single MIGHTYBAG. For bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG will contain a complete bathroom suite, making it the perfect solution for getting rid of waste in one simple operation.\r\n\r\nAll HIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so can easily be stored until needed. In addition, the flexible sides of our bags mean that no void space is created, saving valuable room around your project. The use of a MIGHTYBAG means you pay for an average of 4.77 yds of waste per job, compared with 5.5 – 6 yards in a rigid skip. By using HIPPOWASTE you will be able to save money as well time, benefiting from the most convenient waste solution on the market.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO\'s flexible courier service, there is no need to wait for the arrival or collection of skips, meaning that you can just get on with the job and arrange a collection at a convenient time for you.\r\n\r\nOur customers often save as much as <strong>£70 on each rip-out</strong>. It might not sound a lot – but if you were to do 5,000 installations a year paying the industry standard cost of £175 to dispose of your waste, that would be <strong>a saving of £350,000, or 40%!</strong> At 15,000 installations a year, then that saving rises to <strong>saving of £1,050,000.</strong>','Installation','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 10:46:12','2015-03-12 10:46:12','',12,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/12-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(223,1,'2015-03-11 19:53:57','2015-03-11 19:53:57','The MIGHTYBAG (aka the HIPPOSKIP<sup>TM</sup>) was designed with kitchen and large bathroom installations in mind. The 4.5 cubic yard bag is ideal for light, bulky waste, and can easily accommodate the waste created by a standard kitchen installation. In fact, our customers find that 78% of all kitchen installations fit into a single MIGHTYBAG. For bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG will contain a complete bathroom suite, making it the perfect solution for getting rid of waste in one simple operation.\r\n\r\nAll HIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so can easily be stored until needed. In addition, the flexible sides of our bags mean that no void space is created, saving valuable room around your project. The use of a MIGHTYBAG means you pay for an average of 4.77 yds of waste per job, compared with 5.5 – 6 yards in a rigid skip, this means that you save money as well time by using the most convenient waste solution on the market.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO, there is no need to wait for the arrival or collection of skips, meaning that you can just get on with the job, and arrange a collection at a convenient time for you.\r\n\r\nOur customers often save as much as <strong>£70 on each rip-out</strong>. It might not sound a lot – but if you were to do 5,000 installations a year paying the industry standard cost of £175 to dispose of your waste, that would be <strong>a saving of £350,000, or 40%!</strong> At 15,000 installations a year, then that saving rises to <strong>saving of £1,050,000.</strong>','Installation','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 19:53:57','2015-03-11 19:53:57','',12,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/12-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(131,2,'2015-03-11 11:38:01','2015-03-11 11:38:01','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-97\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"installation-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Installations</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe MIGHTYBAG (aka the HIPPOSKIP<sup>TM</sup>) was designed with kitchen and large bathroom installations in mind. The 4.5 cubic yard bag is ideal for light, bulky waste, and can easily accommodate the waste created by a standard kitchen installation. In fact our customers find that 78% of all kitchen installations fit into a single MIGHTYBAG. For bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG will contain a complete bathroom suite, making it the perfect solution for getting rid of waste in one simple operation.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All HIPPOBAG’s come flat packed, so can easily be stored until needed.</li>\r\n	<li>The flexible sides of the bags mean that no void space is created, preventing wasted space.</li>\r\n	<li>No need to wait for the arrival or collection of skips, just get on with the job.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Saving space</h2>\r\nDue to it’s flexible sides there is less void space than in a traditional skip, the use of a MIGHTYBAG means you pay for an average of 4.77 yds of waste per job, compared with 5.5 – 6 yards in a rigid skip, saving money as well time by as using the most convenient  waste solution on the market.\r\n<h2>Saving money</h2>\r\nOur customers often save as much as <strong>£70 on each rip-out</strong>. It might not sound a lot – but if you were to do 5,000 installations a year paying the industry standard cost of £175 to dispose of your waste, that would be <strong>a saving of £350,000, or 40%!</strong> At 15,000 installations a year, then that saving rises to <strong>saving of £1,050,000.</strong>','Installation','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 11:38:01','2015-03-11 11:38:01','',12,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=131',0,'revision','',0),(206,1,'2015-03-11 18:07:32','2015-03-11 18:07:32','<h1><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-140 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></h1>\r\nGalliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE<img class=\"wp-image-139 size-medium alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/pb-bag-flatty-300x293.png\" alt=\"pb-bag-flatty\" width=\"300\" height=\"293\" /></h2>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\">\r\n</a></blockquote>','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:07:32','2015-03-11 18:07:32','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(134,2,'2015-03-11 11:58:45','2015-03-11 11:58:45','<h1>Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction</h1>\r\nWhere working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAGTM provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store. HIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks. The bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags. Locating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction','Case Study: Interior Fit-Out','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 11:58:45','2015-03-11 11:58:45','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=134',0,'revision','',0),(135,2,'2015-03-11 12:03:53','2015-03-11 12:03:53','<h1>Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction</h1>\r\nWhere working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAGTM provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks. The bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction','Case Study: Interior Fit-Out','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 12:03:53','2015-03-11 12:03:53','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=135',0,'revision','',0),(136,2,'2015-03-11 12:04:22','2015-03-11 12:04:22','<h1>Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction</h1>\r\nWhere working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAGTM provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction','Case Study: Interior Fit-Out','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 12:04:22','2015-03-11 12:04:22','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=136',0,'revision','',0),(137,2,'2015-03-11 12:10:31','2015-03-11 12:10:31','','OFFICEFITOUT','','inherit','open','open','','officefitout','','','2015-03-11 12:10:31','2015-03-11 12:10:31','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/OFFICEFITOUT.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(139,2,'2015-03-11 12:13:11','2015-03-11 12:13:11','','pb-bag-flatty','','inherit','open','open','','pb-bag-flatty','','','2015-03-11 12:13:11','2015-03-11 12:13:11','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/pb-bag-flatty.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(140,2,'2015-03-11 12:14:08','2015-03-11 12:14:08','','INSTALLATIONS2','','inherit','open','open','','installations2','','','2015-03-11 12:14:08','2015-03-11 12:14:08','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(141,2,'2015-03-11 12:15:53','2015-03-11 12:15:53','','Hippostand 014 no pricing','','inherit','open','open','','hippostand-014-no-pricing','','','2015-03-11 12:15:53','2015-03-11 12:15:53','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Hippostand-014-no-pricing.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(142,2,'2015-03-11 12:16:58','2015-03-11 12:16:58','','HOUSINGMAINTENANCE','','inherit','open','open','','housingmaintenance','','','2015-03-11 12:16:58','2015-03-11 12:16:58','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(143,2,'2015-03-11 12:17:42','2015-03-11 12:17:42','HIPPOWASTE™ was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store, is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city. At over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs™ enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source. The bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail','Case Study: Construction','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 12:17:42','2015-03-11 12:17:42','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=143',0,'revision','',0),(144,2,'2015-03-11 12:19:00','2015-03-11 12:19:00','','OFFICEFITOUT','','inherit','open','open','','officefitout-2','','','2015-03-11 12:19:00','2015-03-11 12:19:00','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/OFFICEFITOUT1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(145,2,'2015-03-11 12:19:26','2015-03-11 12:19:26','<h1>Construction with Wates Retail and John Lewis</h1>\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE™ was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store, is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city. At over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs™ enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source. The bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail','Case Study: Construction','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 12:19:26','2015-03-11 12:19:26','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=145',0,'revision','',0),(208,1,'2015-03-11 18:08:06','2015-03-11 18:08:06','<h1><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-140 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></h1>\r\nGalliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\">\r\n</a></blockquote>','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:08:06','2015-03-11 18:08:06','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(146,2,'2015-03-11 12:21:56','2015-03-11 12:21:56','<h1>Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try</h1>\r\n\r\nGalliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard. With the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs™ wi