rd Recycling with Galliford Try</h1>\r\nGalliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.<img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-140\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE<img class=\"wp-image-139 size-medium alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/pb-bag-flatty-300x293.png\" alt=\"pb-bag-flatty\" width=\"300\" height=\"293\" /></h2>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try','Case Study: Plasterboard','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 12:31:30','2015-03-11 12:31:30','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=165',0,'revision','',0),(200,2,'2015-03-11 16:17:21','2015-03-11 16:17:21','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Construction with Wates Retail and John Lewis<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-144 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/OFFICEFITOUT1-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"OFFICEFITOUT\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" /></h1>\r\nHIPPOWASTE was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store, is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city. At over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source. The bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail','Case Study: Construction','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:17:21','2015-03-11 16:17:21','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/32-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(166,2,'2015-03-11 12:31:47','2015-03-11 12:31:47','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Construction with Wates Retail and John Lewis</h1>\r\nHIPPOWASTE was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store, is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city. At over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source. The bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-144 alignnone\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/OFFICEFITOUT1-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"OFFICEFITOUT\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail','Case Study: Construction','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 12:31:47','2015-03-11 12:31:47','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=166',0,'revision','',0),(213,1,'2015-03-11 18:28:16','2015-03-11 18:28:16','<img class=\"  wp-image-142 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"262\" height=\"331\" />Where working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAGTM provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:28:16','2015-03-11 18:28:16','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(170,2,'2015-03-11 13:23:13','2015-03-11 13:23:13','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction</h1>\r\nWhere working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAGTM provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction<img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-158\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction2-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"SAMSUNG DIGITAL CAMERA\" width=\"196\" height=\"196\" /><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-142\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />','Case Study: Interior Fit-Out','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:23:13','2015-03-11 13:23:13','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=170',0,'revision','',0),(167,2,'2015-03-11 12:32:12','2015-03-11 12:32:12','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction</h1>\r\nWhere working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAGTM provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIB<img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-158\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction2-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"SAMSUNG DIGITAL CAMERA\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />AG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-142\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction','Case Study: Interior Fit-Out','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 12:32:12','2015-03-11 12:32:12','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=167',0,'revision','',0),(168,2,'2015-03-11 13:20:58','2015-03-11 13:20:58','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try</h1>\r\nGalliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE<img class=\"wp-image-139 size-medium alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/pb-bag-flatty-300x293.png\" alt=\"pb-bag-flatty\" width=\"300\" height=\"293\" /></h2>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-140\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />','Case Study: Plasterboard','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:20:58','2015-03-11 13:20:58','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=168',0,'revision','',0),(169,2,'2015-03-11 13:22:34','2015-03-11 13:22:34','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try</h1>\r\nGalliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE<img class=\"wp-image-139 size-medium alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/pb-bag-flatty-300x293.png\" alt=\"pb-bag-flatty\" width=\"300\" height=\"293\" /></h2>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-140\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"173\" height=\"173\" />','Case Study: Plasterboard','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:22:34','2015-03-11 13:22:34','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=169',0,'revision','',0),(171,2,'2015-03-11 13:25:15','2015-03-11 13:25:15','','Case Studies','','inherit','open','open','','7-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:25:15','2015-03-11 13:25:15','',7,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=171',0,'revision','',0),(487,0,'2015-04-18 05:42:59','2015-04-18 04:42:59','','Daily backup - April 18, 2015','','publish','open','open','','daily-backup-april-18-2015','','','2015-04-18 05:42:59','2015-04-18 04:42:59','',0,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/daily-backup-april-18-2015/',0,'revisr_commits','',0),(215,1,'2015-03-11 18:30:40','2015-03-11 18:30:40','<h2>Why Choose HIPPO?</h2>\r\nSelecting a waste logistics service is a vital decision for any business. HIPPOWASTE provide a reliable, affordable and convenient national skip alternative for any sized business. Our innovative HIPPOBAG comes in three convenient sizes and is available either online or from our trusted stockists around the UK.\r\n\r\nA HIPPOBAG is the perfect alternative to traditional skip hire for a number of reasons; a HIPPOBAG is bought flat packed and can be used at a convenient time for you, where you would have a limited time if you hired a skip. When you are finished with your HIPPOBAG, simply arrange a collection and our professional couriers will collect your waste and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs also take up very little space and you can suit the size of bag to the size of your project, this means you don’t need to pay the full price that you would for a skip if your needs are smaller.\r\n\r\nHIPPO’s environmental policies mean that you can be reassured that your waste is being handled and disposed of in a responsible manner. We typically recycle around 90% of the waste that we collect. HIPPO are also committed to excellent customer service and have an excellent average customer review rating of 4.7 out of 5.\r\n<h2>Our Waste Logistics Experts</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE provide waste logistics services for a great number of projects. Whether you require waste management in projects such as as new build and construction, housing and renovation, facilities management, kitchen and bathroom installation, retail and office fit out or virtually any project where waste is produced. HIPPOWASTE also run a dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, where we collect uncontaminated plasterboard and recycle 100% of it.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO’s trusted, project–specific approach we can suit our service perfectly to your waste logistics needs, whilst ensuring that you receive value for money and that your waste is dealt with responsibly.','About HIPPOWASTE','','inherit','open','open','','33-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:30:40','2015-03-11 18:30:40','',33,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/33-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(174,2,'2015-03-11 13:36:36','2015-03-11 13:36:36','<h1>About HIPPOWASTE</h1>\r\n<h2>Why Choose HIPPO?</h2>\r\nSelecting a waste logistics service is a vital decision for any business. HIPPOWASTE provide a reliable, affordable and convenient national skip alternative for any sized business. Our innovative HIPPOBAG comes in three convenient sizes and is available either online or from our trusted stockists around the UK.\r\n\r\nA HIPPOBAG is the perfect alternative to traditional skip hire for a number of reasons; a HIPPOBAG is bought flat packed and can be used at a convenient time for you, where you would have a limited time if you hired a skip. When you are finished with your HIPPOBAG, simply arrange a collection and our professional couriers will collect your waste and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs also take up very little space and you can suit the size of bag to the size of your project, this means you don’t need to pay the full price that you would for a skip if your needs are smaller.\r\n\r\nHIPPO’s environmental policies mean that you can be reassured that your waste is being handled and disposed of in a responsible manner. We typically recycle around 90% of the waste that we collect. HIPPO are also committed to excellent customer service and have an excellent average customer review rating of 4.7 out of 5.\r\n<h2>Our Waste Logistics Experts</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE provide waste logistics services for a great number of projects. Whether you require waste management in projects such as as new build and construction, housing and renovation, facilities management, kitchen and bathroom installation, retail and office fit out or virtually any project where waste is produced. HIPPOWASTE also run a dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, where we collect uncontaminated plasterboard and recycle 100% of it.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO’s trusted, project–specific approach we can suit our service perfectly to your waste logistics needs, whilst ensuring that you receive value for money and that your waste is dealt with responsibly.','About HIPPOWASTE','','inherit','open','open','','33-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:36:36','2015-03-11 13:36:36','',33,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=174',0,'revision','',0),(175,2,'2015-03-11 13:36:50','2015-03-11 13:36:50','HIPPO™ is a national provider of innovative and integrated waste logistics solutions, the HIPPOWASTE service caters to the needs of building and construction professionals for their waste removal.\r\n\r\nDriven by the desire to provide an affordable, convenient and reliable waste logistics service for your business, HIPPOWASTE use our innovative yellow HIPPOBAG. These large, strong and convenient skip alternatives are bought flat-packed from either our website of from our trusted retailers, and can be used at a time of your convenience. Once your HIPPOBAG is full, our expert couriers will take it off your hands and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPO take our environmental responsibilities very seriously, recycling 90% of the waste that we collect. In addition, our strong reputation for delivering high standards of customer care in a niche area of the waste logistics market has meant we have experienced significant growth in just seven years of trading.\r\n<h2>Here to Clear</h2>\r\nFor smaller waste logistics needs, HIPPO’s Here to Clear van is ideal. This service is especially suited to areas where access is restricted to waste and where it needs to be manually cleared.\r\n\r\nThese vans carry two of our HIPPO employees, who will ensure that your waste logistics process is carried out seamlessly.  We use a Ford Transit Tipper van for this service, which is able to hold up to 14 yards or a ton of waste. Using this service incurs an additional charge.\r\n<h2>HIPPOPRO</h2>\r\nHIPPOPRO is our service for professional tradesmen, providing the essential tool for your trade. We are trusted by tradesmen around the UK to deliver excellent, affordable and simple service to dispose of your excess waste.\r\n\r\nYou can save space and money by choosing the right sized HIPPOBAG for your business needs, from the 1 yard MIDIBAG, to the 1.5 yard MEGABAG and 4.5 yard HIPPOSKIP. Avoid cluttering up your customers’ driveways with unsightly skips and instead place neat, professional looking HIPPOBAGS at a convenient place for you.\r\n\r\nAs a tradesman you can also enjoy a saving of at least 5% on waste disposal every time that you make a collection with HIPPOPRO.\r\n<h2>Careers at HIPPO</h2>\r\nWe at HIPPO are always looking for new members of our team. If you think you have the skills required to become part of our thriving business, then we may well have a space for you at HIPPO.','About HIPPO','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:36:50','2015-03-11 13:36:50','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?p=175',0,'revision','',0),(176,2,'2015-03-11 13:46:28','2015-03-11 13:46:28','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Retail and Office Fit-out</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer an effective service for use during the refurbishment or fit-out stage of retail and office premises.\r\n\r\nUsing a HIPPOBAG allows you to segregate waste streams on site, making it easy for you to increase your recycling rates, in turn helping you to achieve your diversion from landfill objectives.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGS are a waste logistics solution without the space or time restrictions that you will encounter when either buying a skip or handling waste logistics yourself. With space and time freed up as a result of using HIPPO, your workforce will be more efficient and your business will save money.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer an affordable, flexible and instant waste solution that is both transportable and bespoke to your project. In addition, HIPPOBAGs allow you to carry out the work at a suitable time for you, rather than when you are able to hire a skip, this way you can take greater control of your waste logistics operation and avoid unnecessary hassle during your retail or office fit out project.\r\n\r\nHIPPO’s strong, non-bulky skip alternatives come in three different sizes, so you can match the size of the HIPPOBAG you purchase to the size of the project you are undertaking, meaning that you will never pay for more than you need and will save valuable space around your project.\r\n\r\nRead our retail and office fit-out case study here.','Retail and Offices Fitout','','inherit','open','open','','13-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:46:28','2015-03-11 13:46:28','',13,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/13-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(178,2,'2015-03-11 13:52:15','2015-03-11 13:52:15','<h1>Case Studies</h1>\r\nRead our case studies abou