e for use during the refurbishment or fit-out stage of retail and office premises.\r\n\r\nUsing a HIPPOBAG allows you to segregate waste streams on site, making it easy for you to increase your recycling rates, in turn helping you to achieve your diversion from landfill objectives.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGS are a waste logistics solution without the space or time restrictions that you will encounter when either buying a skip or handling waste logistics yourself. With space and time freed up as a result of using HIPPO, your workforce will be more efficient and your business will save money.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer an affordable, flexible and instant waste solution that is both transportable and bespoke to your project. In addition, HIPPOBAGs allow you to carry out the work at a suitable time for you, rather than when you are able to hire a skip, this way you can take greater control of your waste logistics operation and avoid unnecessary hassle during your retail or office fit out project.\r\n\r\nHIPPO’s strong, non-bulky skip alternatives come in three different sizes, so you can match the size of the HIPPOBAG you purchase to the size of the project you are undertaking, meaning that you will never pay for more than you need and will save valuable space around your project.\r\n\r\nRead our retail and office fit-out case study <a title=\"Case Study: Interior Fit-Out\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/case-study-two/\">here</a>.','Retail and Offices Fitout','','inherit','open','open','','13-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:53:30','2015-03-11 13:53:30','',13,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/13-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(476,2,'2015-04-08 09:47:02','2015-04-08 08:47:02','','facilities-hippo','','inherit','open','open','','facilities','','','2015-04-08 09:47:38','2015-04-08 08:47:38','',14,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(252,2,'2015-03-12 11:10:51','2015-03-12 11:10:51','Using the HIPPOBAG for the segregation of heavy or substantial inert waste streams, or for any unscheduled or ad hoc waste removal needs will benefit your business in a number of ways.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer a professional, reliable and fully national service, meaning that we can manage your waste logistics needs across your entire regional or national store estate. HIPPOWASTE can work alongside any existing contracts that your business has in place, delivering an efficient reconstructed waste logistics operation, should you require more than your current contracts are able to deliver.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE offer a flexible and convenient service that can work around your needs; there are no restricting time limits when using our services and you can arrange a pick up at a suitable time for you.\r\n\r\nOur reputation for facilities management services has meant that thousands of HIPPOBAGs are collected from store estates weekly. We ensure that waste we collect is disposed of in an ethical manner, with over 90 per cent of the waste that we collect being recycled.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs come in three separate sizes and are non-bulky and affordable. Buying the right sized bag for your waste logistics needs will mean that your business will save money, as well as valuable space on site. When used throughout a business on a national or regional store level, significant savings can be made by suiting the size of HIPPOBAGS to your specific needs.','Facilities Management','','inherit','open','open','','14-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:10:51','2015-03-12 11:10:51','',14,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/14-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(225,1,'2015-03-11 19:54:51','2015-03-11 19:54:51','Using the HIPPOBAG for the segregation of heavy or substantial inert waste streams, or for any unscheduled or ad hoc waste logistics needs will benefit your business in a number of ways.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer a national service, so offer a professional service to manage your waste logistics needs across your regional or national store estate. We are able to work alongside any existing waste contracts that your business has in place, ensuring that you receive an efficient reconstructed waste logistics operation, should you require more than your existing contracts are able to deliver.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer a flexible and convenient service that can work around your needs, there are no restricting time limits when using HIPPO and you can arrange a pick up at a suitable time to suit you.\r\n\r\nOur reputation for facilities management services has meant that thousands of HIPPOBAGs are collected from store estates weekly and disposed of in an ethical manner, with around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect being recycled.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs come in three separate sizes and are non-bulky and affordable; buying the right sized skip alternative for your waste logistics needs will ensure that space and money are both saved. When used throughout a business on a national or regional store level, large savings can be made by suiting the size of HIPPOBAGS to the size of your needs. The time saved with our simple, flexible and convenient service will also ensure a more productive workforce, as time saved on waste logistics projects is time gained elsewhere.','Facilities Management','','inherit','open','open','','14-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 19:54:51','2015-03-11 19:54:51','',14,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/14-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(182,2,'2015-03-11 13:53:51','2015-03-11 13:53:51','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities-management-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-95\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities-management-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"facilities-management-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Facilities Management</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUsing the HIPPOBAG for the segregation of heavy or substantial inert waste streams, or for any unscheduled or ad hoc waste logistics needs will benefit your business in a number of ways.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer a national service, so offer a professional service to manage your waste logistics needs across your regional or national store estate. We are able to work alongside any existing waste contracts that your business has in place, ensuring that you receive an efficient reconstructed waste logistics operation, should you require more than your existing contracts are able to deliver.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer a flexible and convenient service that can work around your needs, there are no restricting time limits when using HIPPO and you can arrange a pick up at a suitable time to suit you.\r\n\r\nOur reputation for facilities management services has meant that thousands of HIPPOBAGs are collected from store estates weekly and disposed of in an ethical manner, with around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect being recycled.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs come in three separate sizes and are non-bulky and affordable; buying the right sized skip alternative for your waste logistics needs will ensure that space and money are both saved. When used throughout a business on a national or regional store level, large savings can be made by suiting the size of HIPPOBAGS to the size of your needs. The time saved with our simple, flexible and convenient service will also ensure a more productive workforce, as time saved on waste logistics projects is time gained elsewhere.','Facilities Management','','inherit','open','open','','14-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:53:51','2015-03-11 13:53:51','',14,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/14-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(253,2,'2015-03-12 11:21:25','2015-03-12 11:21:25','HIPPOWASTE can provide quick and reliable service to allow you to remove excess plasterboard from your site. As part of our commitment to responsible and ethical waste logistics, our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme means that we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect.\r\n\r\nIn addition to collecting plasterboard, HIPPO\'s reliable, flexible and convenient service allows the segregation of different types of waste from your project. This means that you can easily increase your company’s recycling rates, as well as saving money on landfill tax.\r\n\r\nHIPPO recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so provide a responsible method of removing waste from your project. We also offer reviews of environmental performance on a site by site basis – including a collection method, a breakdown by waste stream and percentage of landfill diversion.\r\n\r\nWe offer a national waste logistics service, meaning that both regional and national operations are ideally suited to HIPPO. We can handle your entire waste logistics operation, so there is no need for you to deal with several separate companies for your waste needs.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGS are non-bulky and lightweight, meaning that space can be saved on-site whilst you are undertaking your project. In addition to being an affordable price, strong, convenient HIPPOBAGs come in three different sizes, so you can suit the size of HIPPOBAG used for your specific project and save money.\r\n\r\nRead our Plasterboard Recycling case study <a title=\"Case Study: Plasterboard\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/case-study-one/\">here.</a>','Plasterboard Recycling','','inherit','open','open','','15-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:21:25','2015-03-12 11:21:25','',15,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/15-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(226,1,'2015-03-11 19:55:08','2015-03-11 19:55:08','HIPPOWASTE can provide quick and cost effective service to allow you to remove plasterboard from your property as part of your waste logistics operation. As part of our commitment to responsible and ethical waste logistics, our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme means that we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect.\r\n\r\nIn addition to assisting with the removal of plasterboard, our reliable, flexible and convenient service allows the segregation of different types of waste from your project. This means that you can easily increase your company’s recycling rates, as well as saving money on landfill tax.\r\n\r\nHIPPO recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so provide a responsible method of removing waste from your project. We also offer clear reporting of environmental performance on a site by site basis – including a collection method, a breakdown by waste stream and percentage of landfill diversion.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer a national waste logistics service, meaning that both regional and national operations are ideally suited to us. HIPPO can handle your entire waste logistics operation, so there is no need for you to deal with several separate companies for your waste needs and no need to worry about regional variations in skip hire prices.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGS are non-bulky and lightweight, meaning that space can be saved on-site whilst you are undertaking your project. In addition to being an affordable price, strong, convenient HIPPOBAGs come in three different sizes, so you can suit the size of HIPPOBAG used for your specific project and save both space and money.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRead our Plasterboard Recycling case study <a title=\"Case Study: Plasterboard\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/case-study-one/\">here.</a>','Plasterboard Recycling','','inherit','open','open','','15-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 19:55:08','2015-03-11 19:55:08','',15,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/15-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(183,2,'2015-03-11 13:54:39','2015-03-11 13:54:39','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Plasterboard Recycling</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE can provide quick and cost effective service to allow you to remove plasterboard from your property as part of your waste logistics operation. As part of our commitment to responsible and ethical waste logistics, our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme means that we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect.\r\n\r\nIn addition to assisting with the removal of plasterboard, our reliable, flexible and convenient service allows the segregation of different types of waste from your project. This means that you can easily increase your company’s recycling rates, as well as saving money on landfill tax.\r\n\r\nHIPPO recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so provide a responsible method of removing waste from your project. We also offer clear reporting of environmental performance on a site by site basis – including a collection method, a breakdown by waste stream and percentage of landfill diversion.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer a national waste logistics service, meaning that both regional and national operations are ideally suited to us. HIPPO can handle your entire waste logistics operation, so there is no need for you to deal with several separate companies for your waste needs and no need to worry about regional variations in skip hire prices.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGS are non-bulky and lightweight, meaning that space can be saved on-site whilst you are undertaking your project. In addition to being an affordable price, strong, convenient HIPPOBAGs come in three different sizes, so you can suit the size of HIPPOBAG used for your specific project and save both space and money.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRead our Plasterboard Recycling case study <a title=\"Case Study: Plasterboard\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/case-study-one/\">here.</a>','Plasterboard Recycling','','inherit','open','open','','15-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:54:39','2015-03-11 13:54:39','',15,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/15-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(185,2,'2015-03-11 13:57:47','2015-03-11 13:57:47','','all bags','','inherit','open','open','','all-bags','','','2015-03-13 17:33:47','2015-03-13 17:33:47','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/all-bags.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(186,2,'2015-03-11 13:58:22','2015-03-11 13:58:22','HIPPO™ is a national provider of innovative and integrated waste logistics solutions, the HIPPOWASTE service caters to the needs of building and construction professionals for their waste removal.\r\n\r\nDriven bythe desire to provide an affordable, convenient and reliable waste logistics service for your business, HIPPOWASTE use our innovative yellow HIPPOBAG. These large, strong and convenient skip alternatives are bought flat-packed from either our website of from our trusted retailers, and can be used at a time of your convenience. Once your HIPPOBAG is full, our expert couriers will take it off your hands and dispose of it responsibly.<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-185 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/all-bags-300x212.png\" alt=\"all bags\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" />\r\n\r\nHIPPO take our environmental responsibilities very seriously, recycling 90% of the waste that we collect. In addition, our strong reputation for delivering high standards of customer care in a niche area of the waste logistics market has meant we have experienced significant growth in just seven years of trading.\r\n<h2>Here to Clear</h2>\r\nFor smaller waste logistics needs, HIPPO’s Here to Clear van is ideal. This service is especially suited to areas where access is restricted to waste and where it needs to be manually cleared.\r\n\r\nThese vans carry two of our HIPPO employees, who will ensure that your waste logistics process is carried out seamlessly.  We use a Ford Transit Tipper van for this service, which is able to hold up to 14 yards or a ton of waste. Using this service incurs an additional charge.\r\n<h2>HIPPOPRO</h2>\r\nHIPPOPRO is our service for professional tradesmen, providing the essential tool for your trade. We are trusted by tradesmen around the UK to deliver excellent, affordable and simple service to dispose of your excess waste.\r\n\r\nYou can save space and money by choosing the right sized HIPPOBAG for your business needs, from the 1 yard MIDIBAG, to the 1.5 yard MEGABAG and 4.5 yard HIPPOSKIP. Avoid cluttering up your customers’ driveways with unsightly skips and instead place neat, professional looking HIPPOBAGS at a convenient place for you.\r\n\r\nAs a tradesman you can also enjoy a saving of at least 5% on waste disposal every time that you make a collection with HIPPOPRO.\r\n<h2>Careers at HIPPO</h2>\r\nWe at HIPPO are always looking for new members of our team. If you think you have the skills required to become part of our thriving business, then we may well have a space for you at HIPPO.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About HIPPO','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:58:22','2015-03-11 13:58:22','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(187,2,'2015-03-11 13:58:35','2015-03-11 13:58:35','HIPPO™ is a national provider of innovative and integrated waste logistics solutions, the HIPPOWASTE service caters to the needs of building and construction professionals for their waste<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-185 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/all-bags-300x212.png\" alt=\"all bags\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" /> removal.\r\n\r\nDriven bythe desire to provide an affordable, convenient and reliable waste logistics service for your business, HIPPOWASTE use our innovative yellow HIPPOBAG. These large, strong and convenient skip alternatives are bought flat-packed from either our website of from our trusted retailers, and can be used at a time of your convenience. Once your HIPPOBAG is full, our expert couriers will take it off your hands and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPO take our environmental responsibilities very seriously, recycling 90% of the waste that we collect. In addition, our strong reputation for delivering high standards of customer care in a niche area of the waste logistics market has meant we have experienced significant growth in just seven years of trading.\r\n<h2>Here to Clear</h2>\r\nFor smaller waste logistics needs, HIPPO’s Here to Clear van is ideal. This service is especially suited to areas where access is restricted to waste and where it needs to be manually cleared.\r\n\r\nThese vans carry two of our HIPPO employees, who will ensure that your waste logistics process is carried out seamlessly.  We use a Ford Transit Tipper van for this service, which is able to hold up to 14 yards or a ton of waste. Using this service incurs an additional charge.\r\n<h2>HIPPOPRO</h2>\r\nHIPPOPRO is our service for professional tradesmen, providing the essential tool for your trade. We are trusted by tradesmen around the UK to deliver excellent, affordable and simple service to dispose of your excess waste.\r\n\r\nYou can save space and money by choosing the right sized HIPPOBAG for your business needs, from the 1 yard MIDIBAG, to the 1.5 yard MEGABAG and 4.5 yard HIPPOSKIP. Avoid cluttering up your customers’ driveways with unsightly skips and instead place neat, professional looking HIPPOBAGS at a convenient place for you.\r\n\r\nAs a tradesman you can also enjoy a saving of at least 5% on waste disposal every time that you make a collection with HIPPOPRO.\r\n<h2>Careers at HIPPO</h2>\r\nWe at HIPPO are always looking for new members of our team. If you think you have the skills required to become part of our thriving business, then we may well have a space for you at HIPPO.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About HIPPO','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 13:58:35','2015-03-11 13:58:35','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(203,1,'2015-03-11 18:01:03','2015-03-11 18:01:03','HIPPO provide waste logistics services to projects across the construction sector, including social housing, retail and internal fit-out.\r\n\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites around the country use HIPPO because of the lightweight and flexible nature of our convenient HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service and convenience. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, to improve site efficiency.\r\n\r\nHippo can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://www.hippowaste.co.uk/case-studies/plasterboard-recycling\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and improve diversion from landfill, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, to give you flexibility in collection volumes and in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRead our Construction case study <a title=\"Case Study: Construction\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/case-study-three/\">here</a>.','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:01:03','2015-03-11 18:01:03','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(188,2,'2015-03-11 16:10:59','2015-03-11 16:10:59','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Construction</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHIPPO provide waste logistics services to projects across the construction sector, including social housing, retail and internal fit-out.\r\n\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites around the country use HIPPO because of the lightweight and flexible nature of our convenient HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service and convenience. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, to improve site efficiency.\r\n\r\nHippo can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://www.hippowaste.co.uk/case-studies/plasterboard-recycling\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and improve diversion from landfill, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, to give you flexibility in collection volumes and in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRead our Construction case study <a title=\"Case Study: Construction\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/case-study-three/\">here</a>.','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:10:59','2015-03-11 16:10:59','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(221,1,'2015-03-11 19:53:17','2015-03-11 19:53:17','<h1></h1>\r\nEnsuring that existing housing supply across the country is well-maintained and meets a minimum standard of decency is fundamental to healthy and happy communities. HIPPO™ is ideally placed to support refurbishment projects in this vital field.\r\n\r\nWe have a thorough grasp of your challenges in disposing of the waste generated in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods – compounded by operating to strict deadlines and within tight budgets. HIPPO provide a nationwide network for rapid collection, meaning that you can use our services for your waste logistics needs wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer a choice of 3 bag sizes, meaning that we have the perfect bag for you to complete your job. These bags come flat packed, so there is no need to wait for a skip or have to worry about regional skip prices.\r\n\r\nHIPPO has collected over 500,000 bags from domestic properties since 2005. With this level of experience you can be sure of a safe and hassle free collection from your customer’s property. We can also help you to maintain your reputation as a good corporate citizen and fulfil your duty of care to the communities in which you work, by minimising the social and environmental impact of your operations.\r\n\r\nAs well as reducing the direct costs of waste management, we can improve operational efficiencies and minimise disruption and distractions to your core activities. A typical sized homes project produces 2-5 cubic yards of waste from kitchen units, bathroom suites, and central heating systems. HIPPOBAGs, from the 1 cubic yard MIDIBAG to the 4.5 yard MIGHTYBAG, are ideal for the disposal of these waste streams. MEGABAGs were designed to hold a bathroom suite and a single MIGHTYBAG has the capacity to hold both a bathroom suite and a medium kitchen.','Housing and Renovation','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 19:53:17','2015-03-11 19:53:17','',11,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(189,2,'2015-03-11 16:11:17','2015-03-11 16:11:17','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"housing-rennovation-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Housing and Renovation</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEnsuring that existing housing supply across the country is well-maintained and meets a minimum standard of decency is fundamental to healthy and happy communities. HIPPO™ is ideally placed to support refurbishment projects in this vital field.\r\n\r\nWe have a thorough grasp of your challenges in disposing of the waste generated in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods – compounded by operating to strict deadlines and within tight budgets. HIPPO provide a nationwide network for rapid collection, meaning that you can use our services for your waste logistics needs wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer a choice of 3 bag sizes, meaning that we have the perfect bag for you to complete your job. These bags come flat packed, so there is no need to wait for a skip or have to worry about regional skip prices.\r\n\r\nHIPPO has collected over 500,000 bags from domestic properties since 2005. With this level of experience you can be sure of a safe and hassle free collection from your customer’s property. We can also help you to maintain your reputation as a good corporate citizen and fulfil your duty of care to the communities in which you work, by minimising the social and environmental impact of your operations.\r\n\r\nAs well as reducing the direct costs of waste management, we can improve operational efficiencies and minimise disruption and distractions to your core activities. A typical sized homes project produces 2-5 cubic yards of waste from kitchen units, bathroom suites, and central heating systems. HIPPOBAGs, from the 1 cubic yard MIDIBAG to the 4.5 yard MIGHTYBAG, are ideal for the disposal of these waste streams. MEGABAGs were designed to hold a bathroom suite and a single MIGHTYBAG has the capacity to hold both a bathroom suite and a medium kitchen.','Housing and Renovation','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:11:17','2015-03-11 16:11:17','',11,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(190,2,'2015-03-11 16:11:41','2015-03-11 16:11:41','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-97\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"installation-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Installations</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe MIGHTYBAG (aka the HIPPOSKIP<sup>TM</sup>) was designed with kitchen and large bathroom installations in mind. The 4.5 cubic yard bag is ideal for light, bulky waste, and can easily accommodate the waste created by a standard kitchen installation. In fact, our customers find that 78% of all kitchen installations fit into a single MIGHTYBAG. For bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG will contain a complete bathroom suite, making it the perfect solution for getting rid of waste in one simple operation.\r\n\r\nAll HIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so can easily be stored until needed. In addition, the flexible sides of our bags mean that no void space is created, saving valuable room around your project. The use of a MIGHTYBAG means you pay for an average of 4.77 yds of waste per job, compared with 5.5 – 6 yards in a rigid skip, this means that you save money as well time by using the most convenient waste solution on the market.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO, there is no need to wait for the arrival or collection of skips, meaning that you can just get on with the job, and arrange a collection at a convenient time for you.\r\n\r\nOur customers often save as much as <strong>£70 on each rip-out</strong>. It might not sound a lot – but if you were to do 5,000 installations a year paying the industry standard cost of £175 to dispose of your waste, that would be <strong>a saving of £350,000, or 40%!</strong> At 15,000 installations a year, then that saving rises to <strong>saving of £1,050,000.</strong>','Installation','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:11:41','2015-03-11 16:11:41','',12,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/12-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(205,1,'2015-03-11 18:04:54','2015-03-11 18:04:54','<h1><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-140 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></h1>\r\nGalliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE<img class=\"wp-image-139 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/pb-bag-flatty-300x293.png\" alt=\"pb-bag-flatty\" width=\"300\" height=\"293\" /></h2>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\">\r\n</a>','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:04:54','2015-03-11 18:04:54','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(192,2,'2015-03-11 16:13:51','2015-03-11 16:13:51','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try</h1>\r\nGalliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.<img class=\" size-medi