ddev.co.uk/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(194,2,'2015-03-11 16:14:17','2015-03-11 16:14:17','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-140 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></h1>\r\nGalliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE<img class=\"wp-image-139 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/pb-bag-flatty-300x293.png\" alt=\"pb-bag-flatty\" width=\"300\" height=\"293\" /></h2>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\">\r\n</a>','Case Study: Plasterboard','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:14:17','2015-03-11 16:14:17','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(198,2,'2015-03-11 16:16:29','2015-03-11 16:16:29','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction</h1>\r\nWhere working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAGTM provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE.jpg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-142 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"262\" height=\"331\" /></a></h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction','Case Study: Interior Fit-Out','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:16:29','2015-03-11 16:16:29','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(195,2,'2015-03-11 16:15:32','2015-03-11 16:15:32','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction</h1>\r\nWhere working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAGTM provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-158 alignnone\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction2-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"SAMSUNG DIGITAL CAMERA\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />\r\n\r\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-142 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a></h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction','Case Study: Interior Fit-Out','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:15:32','2015-03-11 16:15:32','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(199,2,'2015-03-11 16:16:42','2015-03-11 16:16:42','<h1><a hre