TENANCE-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"262\" height=\"331\" /></a></h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction','Case Study: Interior Fit-Out','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:16:42','2015-03-11 16:16:42','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(196,2,'2015-03-11 16:15:55','2015-03-11 16:15:55','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction</h1>\r\nWhere working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAGTM provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-158 alignnone\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction2-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"SAMSUNG DIGITAL CAMERA\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />The bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-142 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a></h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction','Case Study: Interior Fit-Out','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:15:55','2015-03-11 16:15:55','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(197,2,'2015-03-11 16:16:11','2015-03-11 16:16:11','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction</h1>\r\nWhere working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAGTM provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-158 alignnone\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction2-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"SAMSUNG DIGITAL CAMERA\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />HIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-142 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a></h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction','Case Study: Interior Fit-Out','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:16:11','2015-03-11 16:16:11','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(201,2,'2015-03-11 16:17:36','2015-03-11 16:17:36','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Construction with Wates Retail and John Lewis<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-144 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/OFFICEFITOUT1-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"OFFICEFITOUT\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" /></h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store, is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city.\r\n\r\nAt over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source. The bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail','Case Study: Construction','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:17:36','2015-03-11 16:17:36','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/32-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(214,1,'2015-03-11 18:29:46','2015-03-11 18:29:46','HIPPOWASTE was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store, is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-144 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/OFFICEFITOUT1-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"OFFICEFITOUT\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nAt over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source.\r\n\r\nThe bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Construction with Wates Retail and John Lewis','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:29:46','2015-03-11 18:29:46','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/32-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(202,2,'2015-03-11 16:18:27','2015-03-11 16:18:27','<h1><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"90\" height=\"90\" /></a>Construction with Wates Retail and John Lewis</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store, is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city.<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-144 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/OFFICEFITOUT1-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"OFFICEFITOUT\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nAt over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source.\r\n\r\nThe bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail','Case Study: Construction','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 16:18:27','2015-03-11 16:18:27','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/32-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(204,1,'2015-03-11 18:01:31','2015-03-11 18:01:31','<h2>H2 Test</h2>\r\nHIPPO provide waste logistics services to projects across the construction sector, including social housing, retail and internal fit-out.\r\n\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites around the country use HIPPO because of the lightweight and flexible nature of our convenient HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service and convenience. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, to improve site efficiency.\r\n\r\nHippo can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://www.hippowaste.co.uk/case-studies/plasterboard-recycling\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and improve diversion from landfill, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, to give you flexibility in collection volumes and in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRead our Construction case study <a title=\"Case Study: Construction\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/case-study-three/\">here</a>.','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:01:31','2015-03-11 18:01:31','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(207,1,'2015-03-11 18:07:57','2015-03-11 18:07:57','<h1><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-140 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></h1>\r\nGalliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE<img class=\"wp-image-139 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/pb-bag-flatty-300x293.png\" alt=\"pb-bag-flatty\" width=\"300\" height=\"293\" /></h2>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\">\r\n</a></blockquote>','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:07:57','2015-03-11 18:07:57','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(209,1,'2015-03-11 18:19:58','2015-03-11 18:19:58','Galliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\n\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\n\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\n\n[quote]\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\n\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\">\n</a>\n[/quote]','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-autosave-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:19:58','2015-03-11 18:19:58','',30,'