nt accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\">\r\n</a>\r\n[/quote]','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 18:20:11','2015-03-11 18:20:11','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(219,1,'2015-03-11 19:20:31','2015-03-11 19:20:31','If you have any questions or queries about HIPPOWASTE, we’d love to hear from you!\r\n\r\nYou can get in touch with us via email or phone:\r\nBook Collection: 0345 850 0 850\r\n(Lines Open 08:00 until 18:00 Monday – Friday excluding Bank Holidays)\r\nEmail: sales@hippowaste.co.uk\r\n\r\nIf you are a domestic or DIY customer and are looking for information relating to local stockists or buying your HIPPOBAGS™ online then please visit our newly developed retail website – hippobag.co.uk.\r\n\r\nLet us work with you to design the waste solution that fits your needs and saves you time and money. Enter your contact information below and one of our dedicated Account Managers will call to discuss your project.\r\n\r\nHead Office: HIPPO™, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth, Hampshire, PO6 3EN','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 19:20:31','2015-03-11 19:20:31','',35,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/35-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(216,1,'2015-03-11 19:04:23','2015-03-11 19:04:23','If you have any questions or queries about HIPPOWASTE, we’d love to hear from you!\r\n\r\nYou can get in touch with us via email or phone:\r\nBook Collection: 0345 850 0 850\r\n(Lines Open 08:00 until 18:00 Monday – Friday excluding Bank Holidays)\r\nEmail: sales@hippowaste.co.uk\r\n\r\nIf you are a domestic or DIY customer and are looking for information relating to local stockists or buying your HIPPOBAGS™ online then please visit our newly developed retail website – hippobag.co.uk.\r\n\r\nLet us work with you to design the waste solution that fits your needs and saves you time and money. Enter your contact information below and one of our dedicated Account Managers will call to discuss your project.\r\n\r\n[gravityform id=\"1\" title=\"false\" description=\"false\"]\r\n\r\nHead Office: HIPPO™, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth, Hampshire, PO6 3EN','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 19:04:23','2015-03-11 19:04:23','',35,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/35-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(218,1,'2015-03-11 19:12:40','2015-03-11 19:12:40','If you have any questions or queries about HIPPOWASTE, we’d love to hear from you!\r\n\r\nYou can get in touch with us via email or phone:\r\nBook Collection: 0345 850 0 850\r\n(Lines Open 08:00 until 18:00 Monday – Friday excluding Bank Holidays)\r\nEmail: sales@hippowaste.co.uk\r\n\r\nIf you are a domestic or DIY customer and are looking for information relating to local stockists or buying your HIPPOBAGS™ online then please visit our newly developed retail website – hippobag.co.uk.\r\n\r\nLet us work with you to design the waste solution that fits your needs and saves you time and money. Enter your contact information below and one of our dedicated Account Managers will call to discuss your project.\r\n\r\n[contact-form-7 id=\"217\" title=\"Contact form 1\"]\r\n\r\nHead Office: HIPPO™, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth, Hampshire, PO6 3EN','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 19:12:40','2015-03-11 19:12:40','',35,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/35-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(220,1,'2015-03-11 19:52:46','2015-03-11 19:52:46','The chances are, when you join us, you’ve got more than a job in mind. You’ll be thinking about how joining HIPPO will contribute to your longer term aims – and so will we.\r\n\r\nWe work to provide opportunities for development through both training and through career development. Our training is themed around individuals’ career objectives, departmental requirements, and wider business needs or changes, making sure we’re all ready for our next challenge.\r\n\r\nWe are particularly proud of our team’s career progression – we’re not a huge organisation, but through creative thinking, an eye for talent, and the flexibility that comes with the Company’s growth and development, we have been able to spot opportunities for people to move to roles which are more senior, more challenging, or represent a change of career. This is great for us, as we retain our committed and talented people; and it allows people with talent and ambition to pursue their career aspirations. 9% of our team were promoted into their current roles, and 12% have moved to a different role during their time with HIPPO.\r\n\r\nTo apply for any of vacancies, please email your CV with a covering letter to recruitment@hippowaste.co.uk or post it to: HR Department, HIPPO, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth PO6 3EN\r\n<h2>Current Vacancies</h2>\r\nWe have no current vacancies.','Careers at HIPPOWASTE','','inherit','open','open','','34-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 19:52:46','2015-03-11 19:52:46','',34,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/34-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(222,1,'2015-03-11 19:53:31','2015-03-11 19:53:31','Ensuring that existing housing supply across the country is well-maintained and meets a minimum standard of decency is fundamental to healthy and happy communities. HIPPO™ is ideally placed to support refurbishment projects in this vital field.\r\n\r\nWe have a thorough grasp of your challenges in disposing of the waste generated in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods – compounded by operating to strict deadlines and within tight budgets. HIPPO provide a nationwide network for rapid collection, meaning that you can use our services for your waste logistics needs wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nHIPPO offer a choice of 3 bag sizes, meaning that we have the perfect bag for you to complete your job. These bags come flat packed, so there is no need to wait for a skip or have to worry about regional skip prices.\r\n\r\nHIPPO has collected over 500,000 bags from domestic properties since 2005. With this level of experience you can be sure of a safe and hassle free collection from your customer’s property. We can also help you to maintain your reputation as a good corporate citizen and fulfil your duty of care to the communities in which you work, by minimising the social and environmental impact of your operations.\r\n\r\nAs well as reducing the direct costs of waste management, we can improve operational efficiencies and minimise disruption and distractions to your core activities. A typical sized homes project produces 2-5 cubic yards of waste from kitchen units, bathroom suites, and central heating systems. HIPPOBAGs, from the 1 cubic yard MIDIBAG to the 4.5 yard MIGHTYBAG, are ideal for the disposal of these waste streams. MEGABAGs were designed to hold a bathroom suite and a single MIGHTYBAG has the capacity to hold both a bathroom suite and a medium kitchen.','Housing and Renovation','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 19:53:31','2015-03-11 19:53:31','',11,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(227,1,'2015-03-11 19:55:32','2015-03-11 19:55:32','<strong>Website Terms and Conditions:</strong>\r\n\r\nUse of this website constitutes your acceptance of these terms and conditions, which take effect immediately on your first use of the website. HIPPO reserves the right to add to or change these terms and conditions at any time by posting changes online and it is your responsibility to refer to and comply with these terms on accessing the website. Your continued use of this website after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of these terms and conditions as modified.\r\n\r\nMaterial may not be copied, reproduced, republished, downloaded, posted, broadcast or transmitted in any way except for your own personal non-commercial home use. Any other use requires the prior written permission of HIPPO. You agree not to adapt, alter or create a derivative work from any of the material contained in this website or use it for any other purpose other than for your personal non-commercial use. You agree to use this website only for lawful purposes, and in a manner that does not infringe the rights of, or restrict or inhibit the use and enjoyment of this website by any third party. Such restriction or inhibition includes, without limitation, conduct which is unlawful, or which may harass or cause distress or inconvenience to any person and the transmission of obscene or offensive content or disruption of normal flow of dialogue within this website.\r\n\r\nThe information contained on this website does not, and will not, form any part of a contract or offer for sale. Furthermore it does not constitute an o