2015-03-11 19:55:44','To protect your privacy we provide this notice explaining our online information practices and the choices you can make about the way your information is collected and used.\r\n\r\n1. The information we collect\r\n\r\nThis notice applies to all information collected or submitted on this website. The types of personal information collected on these pages are:\r\n\r\nName\r\nE-mail address\r\nPostal address\r\nTelephone/mobile number\r\n\r\n2. The way we use information\r\n\r\nWe use return e-mail addresses to answer the e-mails we receive. If you request a call back we will use the telephone details provided. If there is a problem with your order we will either telephone or email you to communicate that information with you. The information is not used for any other purpose and is not shared with outside parties.\r\n\r\n3. Our commitment to data security\r\n\r\nWe never use or share the personally identifiable information provided to us online in ways unrelated to those described above without also providing an opportunity for you to opt out or otherwise prohibit such unrelated uses. It will never be supplied to anyone outside HIPPO without first obtaining your consent, unless we are obliged to disclose it by law. To prevent unauthorised access, maintain data accuracy and ensure the correct use of information, we have put in place appropriate physical, electronic and managerial procedures to safeguard and secure the information we collect online. We will ensure that all personal information supplied is held securely, in accordance with the Data Protection Act 1998.\r\n\r\n4. Cookies\r\n\r\nWe may use \'cookies\' for administrative purposes such as cataloguing traffic patterns throughout the website and can use a cookie to assign a \'user ID\' for this purpose. Cookies, by themselves, cannot be used to find out the identity of any user. If you have a user ID this will automatically identify your computer - but not you - to our server when you visit our website. Unless you specifically tell us, we will never know who you are, even if we do assign a cookie to your computer.\r\n\r\n5. Users under 18\r\n\r\nIf you are under 18, please obtain your parent/guardian\'s permission beforehand whenever you provide personal information to HIPPO\'s website. Users without this consent are not allowed to provide us with personal information.\r\n\r\nThird party vendors including Google will show adverts on sites across the internet. To opt out or alter your settings click here Ads Preferences Manager\r\n\r\nWe (hippowaste.co.uk) and third-party vendors, including Google, use first-party cookies (such as the Google Analytics cookie) and third-party cookies (such as the DoubleClick cookie) together to inform, optimize, and serve ads based on someone\'s past visits to your website.','Privacy Policy','','publish','open','open','','privacy-policy','','','2015-06-05 16:04:49','2015-06-05 15:04:49','',0,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?page_id=229',0,'page','',0),(573,2,'2015-06-05 16:04:49','2015-06-05 15:04:49','To protect your privacy we provide this notice explaining our online information practices and the choices you can make about the way your information is collected and used.\r\n\r\n1. The information we collect\r\n\r\nThis notice applies to all information collected or submitted on this website. The types of personal information collected on these pages are:\r\n\r\nName\r\nE-mail address\r\nPostal address\r\nTelephone/mobile number\r\n\r\n2. The way we use information\r\n\r\nWe use return e-mail addresses to answer the e-mails we receive. If you request a call back we will use the telephone details provided. If there is a problem with your order we will either telephone or email you to communicate that information with you. The information is not used for any other purpose and is not shared with outside parties.\r\n\r\n3. Our commitment to data security\r\n\r\nWe never use or share the personally identifiable information provided to us online in ways unrelated to those described above without also providing an opportunity for you to opt out or otherwise prohibit such unrelated uses. It will never be supplied to anyone outside HIPPO without first obtaining your consent, unless we are obliged to disclose it by law. To prevent unauthorised access, maintain data accuracy and ensure the correct use of information, we have put in place appropriate physical, electronic and managerial procedures to safeguard and secure the information we collect online. We will ensure that all personal information supplied is held securely, in accordance with the Data Protection Act 1998.\r\n\r\n4. Cookies\r\n\r\nWe may use \'cookies\' for administrative purposes such as cataloguing traffic patterns throughout the website and can use a cookie to assign a \'user ID\' for this purpose. Cookies, by themselves, cannot be used to find out the identity of any user. If you have a user ID this will automatically identify your computer - but not you - to our server when you visit our website. Unless you specifically tell us, we will never know who you are, even if we do assign a cookie to your computer.\r\n\r\n5. Users under 18\r\n\r\nIf you are under 18, please obtain your parent/guardian\'s permission beforehand whenever you provide personal information to HIPPO\'s website. Users without this consent are not allowed to provide us with personal information.\r\n\r\nThird party vendors including Google will show adverts on sites across the internet. To opt out or alter your settings click here Ads Preferences Manager\r\n\r\nWe (hippowaste.co.uk) and third-party vendors, including Google, use first-party cookies (such as the Google Analytics cookie) and third-party cookies (such as the DoubleClick cookie) together to inform, optimize, and serve ads based on someone\'s past visits to your website.','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','229-revision-v1','','','2015-06-05 16:04:49','2015-06-05 15:04:49','',229,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/229-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(230,1,'2015-03-11 19:55:44','2015-03-11 19:55:44','','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','229-revision-v1','','','2015-03-11 19:55:44','2015-03-11 19:55:44','',229,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/229-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(494,2,'2015-04-30 11:55:24','2015-04-30 10:55:24','<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Plasterboard-Service-Image.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-493 size-full\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Plasterboard-Service-Image.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"563\" height=\"773\" /></a>Galliford Try used the HIPPOBAG system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h3>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h3>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-04-30 11:55:24','2015-04-30 10:55:24','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(408,1,'2015-03-23 06:30:58','2015-03-23 06:30:58','<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/galliford-try-plasterboard.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-395\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/galliford-try-plasterboard.jpg\" alt=\"Galliford Try Plasterboard HIPPO\" width=\"331\" height=\"500\" /></a>Galliford Try used the HIPPOBAG system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h3>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h3>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-23 06:30:58','2015-03-23 06:30:58','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(442,0,'2015-03-29 18:27:25','2015-03-29 17:27:25','','Daily backup - March 29, 2015','','publish','open','open','','daily-backup-march-29-2015','','','2015-03-29 18:27:25','2015-03-29 17:27:25','',0,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/daily-backup-march-29-2015/',0,'revisr_commits','',0),(244,1,'2015-03-12 07:55:50','2015-03-12 07:55:50','Thank you for getting in touch. A member of our team will be in touch shortly to discuss your needs.','Success','','publish','open','open','','success','','','2015-03-12 07:55:50','2015-03-12 07:55:50','',0,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/?page_id=244',0,'page','',0),(245,1,'2015-03-12 07:55:50','2015-03-12 07:55:50','Thank you for getting in touch. A member of our team will be in touch shortly to discuss your needs.','Success','','inherit','open','open','','244-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 07:55:50','2015-03-12 07:55:50','',244,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/244-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(283,2,'2015-06-01 11:07:54','2015-06-01 10:07:54','Choosing a waste logistics company is a vital decision. Not only do you need a service that’s professional, affordable and environmentally responsible, you require a solution that takes care of everything from collection to disposal, so you’re free to focus on your project.\n\nWhen you choose HIPPOWASTE you know you will benefit from:\n<ul>\n	<li>a nationwide network for rapid collection</li>\n	<li>competitive pricing and market leading service</li>\n	<li>over 90% of your waste being recycled</li>\n	<li>valuable time and space saved on site, as you only use the space you need</li>\n</ul>\nAt HIPPO, we provide bespoke and reliable waste solutions that help you reduce costs, save time, and meet your environmental responsibilities.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> <a title=\"Construction\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/construction/\">Construction Waste</a></h2>\nThe construction industry is the single largest producer of waste in the UK, generating some 120 million tonnes of waste annually. We understand that a variety of waste can be produced in construction tasks, and ensure that all types of waste, including plasterboard, are dealt with responsibly and efficiently in our waste logistics projects.\n\nWith HIPPO, you only have to deal with one supplier for all of your waste disposal needs, meaning that we can develop a bespoke solution for your specific challenges – giving you maximum efficiency and flexibility even in the largest of construction waste logistics tasks.\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-95\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities-management-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"facilities-management-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> <a title=\"Facilities Management\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/facilities-management/\">Facilities Management</a></h2>\nUsing the HIPPOBAG to deal with heavy or bulk inert waste streams and ad hoc waste events will provide you with a number of benefits in managing waste disposal across your national or regional store estate. By working together with any existing waste contracts you have, we can assist you in reshaping your waste services.\n\nOur service is not a regular scheduled waste collection covered by a bin contract, so you can use us for unexpected waste events whenever you need us. With thousands of HIPPOBAGs collected from store estates weekly, HIPPO provides a flexible, convenient and ethical service for your business.\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"housing-rennovation-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> <a title=\"Housing and Renovation\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/housing-and-renovation/\">Housing and Renovation</a></h2>\nWe have collected over half a million HIPPOBAGs from residential properties, so we understand the challenges of waste disposal in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods.\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> <a title=\"Retail and Office Fit-out\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/retail-and-offices-fitout/\">Retail and Office Fitout</a></h2>\nDuring the refurbishment or fit out stage of retail and office premises, using a HIPPOBAG allows you to segregate waste streams on site, helping you to achieve increased recycling rates. This in return helps you to achieve your diversion from landfill objectives.\n\nWith HIPPOWASTE you’ll also benefit from the flexibility of an instant and non-bulky waste solution that is transportable and bespoke to your project. HIPPOWASTE works around your business, with our flat packed bags able to be used at any time, as well as being collected at a time of your convenience. This way you no longer have to wait for skip deliveries or collections that clutter sites, hampering the progress of your workforce.\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> <a title=\"Plasterboard Recycling\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/plasterboard-recycling/\">Plasterboard Recycling</a></h2>\nHIPPOWASTE also offers a quick and cost effective way of getting rid of plasterboard from your site or property. Through our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect. HIPPO’s environmental values mean that by using our services, you can ensure that you are disposing of your waste in a responsible and eco-friendly manner.\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-97\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"installation-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> <a title=\"Installation\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/installation/\">Installations</a></h2>\nHIPPOWASTE offers an ideal service for kitchen, bathroom, installations. We understand the importance of minimising inconvenience to customers and their surrounding properties during a domestic remodelling. HIPPO cause the least possible disruption to your customers by ensuring that waste is kept neatly and takes up as little room as possible on site.\n\nHIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so don’t take up room before they are used.\n\n&nbsp;','Business Solutions','','inherit','open','open','','6-autosave-v1','','','2015-06-01 11:07:54','2015-06-01 10:07:54','',6,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/6-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(277,2,'2015-03-13 11:51:29','2015-03-13 11:51:29','Choosing a waste logistics company is a vital decision. Not only do you need a service that’s professional, affordable and environmentally responsible; you require a solution that takes care of everything from collection to disposal, so you’re free to focus on your project.\r\n\r\nWhen you choose HIPPOWASTE you know you will benefit from:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>a nationwide network for rapid collection</li>\r\n	<li>competitive pricing and market leading service</li>\r\n	<li>over 90% of your waste being recycled</li>\r\n	<li>valuable time and space saved on site, as you only use the space you need</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAt HIPPO, we provide bespoke and reliable waste solutions that help you reduce costs, save time, and meet your environmental responsibilities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Construction Waste</h2>\r\nThe construction industry is the single largest producer of waste in the UK, generating some 120 million tonnes of waste annually. We understand that a variety of waste can be produced in construction tasks, and ensure that even hazardous waste and plasterboard are dealt with responsibly and efficiently in our waste logistics projects.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO, you only have to deal with one supplier for all of your waste disposal needs, meaning that we can develop a bespoke solution for your specific challenges – giving you maximum efficiency and flexibility even in the largest of construction waste logistics tasks.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-95\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities-management-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"facilities-management-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Facilities Management</h2>\r\nUsing the HIPPOBAG to deal with heavy or bulk inert waste streams and ad hoc waste events will provide you with a number of benefits in managing waste disposal across your national or regional store estate. By working together with any existing waste contracts you have, we can assist you in reconstructing your waste services.\r\n\r\nOur service is not a regular scheduled waste collection covered by a bin contract, so you can use us for unexpected waste events whenever you need us. With thousands of HIPPOBAGS collected from store estates weekly, HIPPO provides a flexible, convenient and ethical service for your business.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"housing-rennovation-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Housing and Renovation</h2>\r\nWe have collected over half a million HIPPOBAGs from residential properties, so we understand the challenges of waste disposal in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Retail and Office Fitout</h2>\r\nDuring the refurbishment or fit out stage of retail and office premises, using a HIPPOBAG allows you to segregate waste streams on site, helping you to achieve increased recycling rates. This in return helps you to achieve your diversion from landfill objectives.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPOWASTE you’ll also benefit from the flexibility of an instant and non-bulky waste solution that is transportable and bespoke to your project. HIPPOWASTE work around your business, with our flat packed bags able to be used at any time – up to a year –after purchase, as well as being collected at a time of your convenience. This way you no-longer have to wait for skip deliveries or collections that clutter sites, hampering the progress of your workforce.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Plasterboard Recycling</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE also offer a quick and cost effective way of getting rid of plasterboard from your site or property. Through our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect. HIPPO’s environmental values mean that by using our services, you can ensure that you are disposing of your waste in a responsible and eco-friendly manner.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-97\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"installation-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Installations</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE offers an ideal service for installations. We understand the importance of minimising inconvenience to customers and their surrounding properties during a domestic remodelling. HIPPO cause the least possible disruption to your customers by ensuring that waste is kept neatly and takes up as little room as possible on site.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so don’t waste room before they are used. In addition, our reliable and flexible courier service means that you can arrange for your HIPPOBAG to be picked up at a convenient time for you. HIPPOBAGS can also be left on your – or your customer’s – property, making them far more tidy and convenient than a traditional skip that would be left on the road.\r\n\r\nFor bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG is ideal, able to hold an entire bathroom suite. The larger 4.5 Yard HIPPOSKIP was developed to accommodate kitchen and larger bathroom installation projects.','Services','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 11:51:29','2015-03-13 11:51:29','',6,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(247,2,'2015-03-12 10:20:14','2015-03-12 10:20:14','Choosing a waste logistics company is a vital decision. Not only do you need a service that’s professional, affordable and environmentally responsible; you require a solution that takes care of everything from collection to disposal, so you’re free to focus on your project.\r\n\r\nWhen you choose HIPPOWASTE you know you will benefit from:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>a nationwide network for rapid collection</li>\r\n	<li>competitive pricing and market leading service</li>\r\n	<li>over 90% of your waste being recycled</li>\r\n	<li>valuable time and space saved on site, as you only use the space you need</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAt HIPPO, we provide bespoke and reliable waste solutions that help you reduce costs, save time, and meet your environmental responsibilities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /></a> Construction Waste</h2>\r\nThe construction industry is the single largest producer of waste in the UK, generating some 120 million tonnes of waste annually. We understand that a variety of waste can be produced in construction tasks, and ensure that even hazardous waste and plasterboard are dealt with responsibly and efficiently in our waste logistics projects.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO, you only have to deal with one supplier for all of your waste disposal needs, meaning that we can develop a bespoke solution for your specific challenges – giving you maximum efficiency and flexibility even in the largest of construction waste logistics tasks.\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities-management-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-95\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities-management-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"facilities-management-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /></a> Facilities Management</h2>\r\nUsing the HIPPOBAG to deal with heavy or bulk inert waste streams and ad hoc waste events will provide you with a number of benefits in managing waste disposal across your national or regional store estate. By working together with any existing waste contracts you have, we can assist you in reconstructing your waste services.\r\n\r\nOur service is not a regular scheduled waste collection covered by a bin contract, so you can use us for unexpected waste events whenever you need us. With thousands of HIPPOBAGS collected from store estates weekly, HIPPO provides a flexible, convenient and ethical service for your business.\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"housing-rennovation-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /></a> Housing and Renovation</h2>\r\nWe have collected over half a million HIPPOBAGs from residential properties, so we understand the challenges of waste disposal in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods.\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /></a> Retail and Office Fitout</h2>\r\nDuring the refurbishment or fit out stage of retail and office premises, using a HIPPOBAG allows you to segregate waste streams on site, helping you to achieve increased recycling rates. This in return helps you to achieve your diversion from landfill objectives.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPOWASTE you’ll also benefit from the flexibility of an instant and non-bulky waste solution that is transportable and bespoke to your project. HIPPOWASTE work around your business, with our flat packed bags able to be used at any time – up to a year –after purchase, as well as being collected at a time of your convenience. This way you no-longer have to wait for skip deliveries or collections that clutter sites, hampering the progress of your workforce.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Plasterboard Recycling</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE also offer a quick and cost effective way of getting rid of plasterboard from your site or property. Through our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect. HIPPO’s environmental values mean that by using our services, you can ensure that you are disposing of your waste in a responsible and eco-friendly manner.\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-97\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"installation-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /></a> Installations</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE offers an ideal service for installations. We understand the importance of minimising inconvenience to customers and their surrounding properties during a domestic remodelling. HIPPO cause the least possible disruption to your customers by ensuring that waste is kept neatly and takes up as little room as possible on site.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so don’t waste room before they are used. In addition, our reliable and flexible courier service means that you can arrange for your HIPPOBAG to be picked up at a convenient time for you. HIPPOBAGS can also be left on your – or your customer’s – property, making them far more tidy and convenient than a traditional skip that would be left on the road.\r\n\r\nFor bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG is ideal, able to hold an entire bathroom suite. The larger 4.5 Yard HIPPOSKIP was developed to accommodate kitchen and larger bathroom installation projects.','Services','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 10:20:14','2015-03-12 10:20:14','',6,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(280,2,'2015-03-13 12:11:59','2015-03-13 12:11:59','HIPPOWASTE can provide quick and reliable service to allow you to remove excess plasterboard from your site. As part of our commitment to responsible and ethical waste logistics, our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme means that we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect.\r\n\r\nIn addition to collecting plasterboard, HIPPO\'s reliable, flexible and convenient service allows the segregation of different types of waste from your project. This means that you can easily increase your company’s recycling rates, as well as saving money on landfill tax.\r\n\r\nHIPPO recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so provide a responsible method of removing waste from your project. We also offer reviews of environmental performance on a site by site basis – including a collection method, a breakdown by waste stream and percentage of landfill diversion.\r\n\r\nWe offer a national waste logistics service, meaning that both regional and national operations are ideally suited to HIPPO. We can handle your entire waste logistics operation, so there is no need for you to deal with several separate companies for your waste needs.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGS are non-bulky and lightweight, meaning that space can be saved on-site whilst you are undertaking your project. In addition to being an affordable price, strong, convenient HIPPOBAGs come in three different sizes, so you can suit the size of HIPPOBAG used for your specific project and save money.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/plasterboard-recycling-case-study/\">Read our Plasterboard Recycling case study here.</a>','Plasterboard Recycling','','inherit','open','open','','15-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 12:11:59','2015-03-13 12:11:59','',15,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/15-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(281,2,'2015-03-13 12:14:31','2015-03-13 12:14:31','HIPPO provide waste logistics services to projects across the construction sector, including social housing, retail and internal fit-out.\r\n\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites nationwide use HIPPO because of the convenience and reliability of our lightweight and flexible HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, helping you to improve site efficiency.\r\n\r\nHIPPO can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all of your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/plasterboard-recycling/\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and achieve diversion from landfill objectives, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, giving you flexibility in collection volumes, as well as in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/construction-case-study/\">Read our Construction case study here</a>.','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 12:14:31','2015-03-13 12:14:31','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(248,2,'2015-03-12 10:30:58','2015-03-12 10:30:58','<h2>H2 Test</h2>\r\nHIPPO provide waste logistics services to projects across the construction sector, including social housing, retail and internal fit-out.\r\n\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites nationwide use HIPPO because of the convenience and reliability of our lightweight and flexible HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, helping you to improve site efficiency.\r\n\r\nHIPPO can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all of your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://www.hippowaste.co.uk/case-studies/plasterboard-recycling\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and achieve diversion from landfill objectives, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, giving you flexibility in collection volumes, as well as in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRead our Construction case study <a title=\"Case Study: Construction\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/case-study-three/\">here</a>.','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 10:30:58','2015-03-12 10:30:58','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(249,2,'2015-03-12 10:39:22','2015-03-12 10:39:22','Ensuring that existing housing supply across the country is well-maintained and meets a minimum standard of decency is fundamental to healthy and happy communities. HIPPO™ is ideally placed to support refurbishment projects in this vital field.\r\n\r\nWe have a thorough grasp of the challenges in disposing of waste generated in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods – compounded by operating to strict deadlines and within tight budgets.\r\n\r\nHIPPO has collected over 500,000 bags from domestic properties since 2005. With this level of experience you can be sure of a safe and hassle free collection from your customer’s property. We can also help you to maintain your reputation as a good corporate citizen and fulfil your duty of care to the communities in which you work, by minimising the social and environmental impact of your operations.\r\n\r\nHIPPO provide a nationwide network for rapid collection, meaning that you can use our services for your waste logistics needs wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nWe offer a choice of 3 bag sizes, meaning that whatever size project you\'re undertaking, we have the perfect bag for you to complete your job. These bags come flat packed, so there is no need to wait for a skip or have to worry about regional skip prices and availability.\r\n\r\nAs well as reducing the direct costs of waste management, we can improve operational efficiencies and minimise disruption and distractions to your core activities. A typical sized homes project produces 2-5 cubic yards of waste from kitchen units, bathroom suites, and central heating systems. HIPPOBAGs, from the 1 cubic yard MIDIBAG to the 4.5 yard MIGHTYBAG, are ideal for the disposal of these waste streams. MEGABAGs were designed to hold a bathroom suite and a single MIGHTYBAG has the capacity to hold both a bathroom suite and a medium kitchen.','Housing and Renovation','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 10:39:22','2015-03-12 10:39:22','',11,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(255,2,'2015-03-12 11:24:02','2015-03-12 11:24:02','<h1>Case Studies</h1>\r\nRead our case studies about the effectiveness of HIPPOWASTE, and learn how we could help your business:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"75\" height=\"75\" /></a>Construction</h2>\r\nWates Retails used the HIPPOWASTE service for the construction of Liverpool\'s John Lewis store, with huge success.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"75\" height=\"75\" /></a>Office &amp; Retail Fit-Out</h2>\r\nThe HIPPOWASTE service assisted in the Fit-Out of John Lewis alongside McLaren Construction.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon.png\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"75\" height=\"75\" /></a>Plasterboard</h2>\r\nGalliford Try had some tricky plasterboard removal which they needed HIPPO\'s help with.','Case Studies','','inherit','open','open','','7-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:24:02','2015-03-12 11:24:02','',7,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/7-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(257,2,'2015-03-12 11:31:19','2015-03-12 11:31:19','<img class=\"  wp-image-142 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"262\" height=\"331\" />Where working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAG provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele. Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:31:19','2015-03-12 11:31:19','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(411,1,'2015-03-23 06:32:06','2015-03-23 06:32:06','<img class=\"alignright wp-image-400\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/contruction-casestudy.jpg\" alt=\"Construction Casestudy HIPPO\" width=\"368\" height=\"550\" />HIPPOWASTE was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAt over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors, making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source.\r\n\r\nThe bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor, where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h3>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h3>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Construction with Wates Retail and John Lewis','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-03-23 06:32:06','2015-03-23 06:32:06','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/32-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(260,2,'2015-03-12 11:35:23','2015-03-12 11:35:23','HIPPOWASTE was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-144 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/OFFICEFITOUT1-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"OFFICEFITOUT\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nAt over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors, making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source.\r\n\r\nThe bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor, where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h2>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Construction with Wates Retail and John Lewis','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:35:23','2015-03-12 11:35:23','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/32-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(261,2,'2015-03-12 11:36:12','2015-03-12 11:36:12','<img class=\"  wp-image-142 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"262\" height=\"331\" />Where working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAG provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h2>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE</h2>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele, Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:36:12','2015-03-12 11:36:12','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(262,1,'2015-03-12 11:42:39','2015-03-12 11:42:39','HIPPO provide waste logistics services to projects across the construction sector, including social housing, retail and internal fit-out.\r\n\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites nationwide use HIPPO because of the convenience and reliability of our lightweight and flexible HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, helping you to improve site efficiency.\r\n\r\nHIPPO can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all of your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://www.hippowaste.co.uk/case-studies/plasterboard-recycling\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and achieve diversion from landfill objectives, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, giving you flexibility in collection volumes, as well as in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRead our Construction case study <a title=\"Case Study: Construction\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/case-study-three/\">here</a>.','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:42:39','2015-03-12 11:42:39','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(263,2,'2015-03-12 11:44:29','2015-03-12 11:44:29','HIPPO™ is a national provider of innovative and integrated waste logistics solutions, the HIPPOWASTE service caters to the needs of building and construction professionals for their waste<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-185 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/all-bags-300x212.png\" alt=\"all bags\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" /> removal.\r\n\r\nDriven by the desire to provide an affordable, convenient and reliable waste logistics service for your business, HIPPOWASTE use our innovative yellow HIPPOBAG. These large, strong and convenient skip alternatives are bought flat-packed from either our website or our trusted retailers and can be used at a time of your convenience. Once your HIPPOBAG is full, our expert couriers will take it off your hands and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPO take our environmental responsibilities very seriously, recycling 90% of the waste that we collect. In addition, our strong reputation for delivering high standards of customer care in a niche area of the waste logistics market has meant we have experienced significant growth in just seven years of trading.\r\n<h2>Here to Clear</h2>\r\nFor smaller waste logistics needs, HIPPO’s Here to Clear van is ideal. This service is especially suited to areas where access is restricted to waste and where it needs to be manually cleared.\r\n\r\nThese vans carry two of our HIPPO employees, who will ensure that your waste logistics process is carried out seamlessly.  We use a Ford Transit Tipper van for this service, which is able to hold up to 14 yards - or a tonne - of waste. Using this service incurs an additional charge.\r\n<h2>HIPPOPRO</h2>\r\nHIPPOPRO is our service for professional tradesmen, providing the essential tool for your trade. We are trusted by tradesmen around the UK to deliver a reliable, affordable and simple service to dispose of your excess waste.\r\n\r\nYou can save space and money by choosing the right sized HIPPOBAG for your business needs, from the 1 yard MIDIBAG, to the 1.5 yard MEGABAG and 4.5 yard HIPPOSKIP. Avoid cluttering up your customers’ driveways with unsightly skips and instead place neat, professional looking HIPPOBAGS at a convenient place for you.\r\n\r\nAs a tradesman you can also enjoy a saving of at least 5% on waste disposal every time that you make a collection with HIPPOPRO.\r\n<h2>Careers at HIPPO</h2>\r\nWe at HIPPO are always on the look out for new people to join our team. If you think you have the skills required to become part of our thriving waste logistics business, then we may well have a space for you at HIPPO.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About HIPPO','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:44:29','2015-03-12 11:44:29','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(265,1,'2015-03-12 11:47:11','2015-03-12 11:47:11','<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-140 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>Galliford Try used the HIPPOBAG™ system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs™ made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h3>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h3>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\">\r\n</a>\r\n[/quote]','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:47:11','2015-03-12 11:47:11','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(266,1,'2015-03-12 11:47:29','2015-03-12 11:47:29','<img class=\"  wp-image-142 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/HOUSINGMAINTENANCE-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"HOUSINGMAINTENANCE\" width=\"262\" height=\"331\" />Where working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAG provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\r\n\r\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\r\n\r\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h3>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE</h3>\r\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\r\n\r\nLeigh Steele, Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:47:29','2015-03-12 11:47:29','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(267,1,'2015-03-12 11:47:49','2015-03-12 11:47:49','HIPPOWASTE was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-144 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/OFFICEFITOUT1-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"OFFICEFITOUT\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nAt over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors, making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source.\r\n\r\nThe bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor, where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h3>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h3>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Construction with Wates Retail and John Lewis','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:47:49','2015-03-12 11:47:49','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/32-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(268,2,'2015-03-12 11:55:43','2015-03-12 11:55:43','<h2>Why Choose HIPPO?</h2>\r\nSelecting a waste logistics service is a vital decision for any business. HIPPOWASTE provide a reliable, affordable and convenient national skip alternative for any sized business. Our innovative HIPPOBAG comes in three convenient sizes and is available either online or from our trusted stockists around the UK.\r\n\r\nA HIPPOBAG is the perfect alternative to traditional skip hire for a number of reasons; a HIPPOBAG is bought flat packed and can be used at a convenient time for you, where you would have a limited time if you hired a skip. When you are finished with your HIPPOBAG, simply arrange a collection and our professional couriers will collect your waste and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs also take up very little space, and you can suit the size of bag to the specific needs of your project; this means you don’t need to pay the full price that you would for a skip if your needs are smaller. You can also segregate waste into different streams using HIPPOBAGs, allowing you to increase recycling rates.\r\n\r\nHIPPO’s environmental policies mean you can rest assured that your waste is being handled and disposed of in a responsible manner. We typically recycle around 90% of the waste that we collect. HIPPO are also committed to excellent customer service and have an average customer review rating of 4.7 out of 5.\r\n<h2>Our Waste Logistics Experts</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE provide waste logistics services for a huge variety of projects. Whether you require waste logistics in new build and construction, housing and renovation, facilities management, kitchen and bathroom installation, retail and office fit out or virtually any waste-producing project; HIPPO offer the ideal service for your needs.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE also run a dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, where we collect uncontaminated plasterboard and recycle 100% of it.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO’s trusted, flexible and project–specific approach, we can suit our services perfectly to your waste logistics needs, whilst ensuring that you receive value for money and  that your waste is dealt with responsibly.','About HIPPOWASTE','','inherit','open','open','','33-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:55:43','2015-03-12 11:55:43','',33,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/33-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(406,2,'2015-03-16 11:41:23','2015-03-16 11:41:23','<img class=\"alignright wp-image-321\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/careers1.jpg\" alt=\"careers\" width=\"455\" height=\"410\" />The chances are, when you join us, you\'ve got more than a job in mind. You’ll be thinking about how joining HIPPO will contribute to your longer term aims – and so will we.\r\n<h2>opportunities</h2>\r\nWe work to provide opportunities for development through both training and through career development. Our training is themed around individuals’ career objectives, departmental requirements, and wider business needs or changes, making sure we’re all ready for our next challenge.\r\n<h2>progression</h2>\r\nWe are particularly proud of our team’s career progression – we’re not a huge organisation, but through creative thinking, an eye for talent, and the flexibility that comes with the Company’s growth and development, we have been able to spot opportunities for people to move to roles which are more senior, more challenging, or represent a change of career. This is great for us, as we retain our committed and talented people; and it allows people with talent and ambition to pursue their career aspirations. 9% of our team were promoted into their current roles, and 12% have moved to a different role during their time with HIPPO.\r\n<h2>how to apply</h2>\r\nTo apply for any of vacancies, please email your CV with a covering letter to recruitment@hippowaste.co.uk or post it to: HR Department, HIPPO, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth PO6 3EN\r\n<h2>Current Vacancies</h2>\r\nWe have no current vacancies.','Careers at HIPPOWASTE','','inherit','open','open','','34-revision-v1','','','2015-03-16 11:41:23','2015-03-16 11:41:23','',34,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/34-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(270,2,'2015-03-12 11:59:51','2015-03-12 11:59:51','If you have any questions or queries about HIPPOWASTE, we’d love to hear from you!\r\n\r\nYou can get in touch with us via email or phone:\r\nBook Collection: 0345 850 0 850\r\n(Lines Open 08:00 until 18:00 Monday – Friday excluding Bank Holidays)\r\nEmail: sales@hippowaste.co.uk\r\n\r\nIf you are a domestic or DIY customer and are looking for information relating to local stockists or buying your HIPPOBAGS™ online then please visit our newly developed retail website – hippobag.co.uk\r\n\r\nLet us work with you to design the waste solution that fits your needs and saves you time and money. Enter your contact information below and one of our dedicated Account Managers will call to discuss your project.\r\n\r\nHead Office: HIPPO™, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth, Hampshire, PO6 3EN','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-v1','','','2015-03-12 11:59:51','2015-03-12 11:59:51','',35,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/35-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(271,2,'2015-03-13 10:52:08','2015-03-13 10:52:08','Ensuring that existing housing supply across the country is well-maintained and meets a minimum standard of decency is fundamental to healthy and happy communities. HIPPO is ideally placed to support refurbishment projects in this vital field.\r\n\r\nWe have a thorough grasp of the challenges in disposing of waste generated in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods – compounded by operating to strict deadlines and within tight budgets.\r\n\r\nHIPPO has collected over 500,000 bags from domestic properties since 2005. With this level of experience you can be sure of a safe and hassle free collection from your customer’s property. We can also help you to maintain your reputation as a good corporate citizen and fulfil your duty of care to the communities in which you work, by minimising the social and environmental impact of your operations.\r\n\r\nHIPPO provide a nationwide network for rapid collection, meaning that you can use our services for your waste logistics needs wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nWe offer a choice of 3 bag sizes, meaning that whatever size project you\'re undertaking, we have the perfect bag for you to complete your job. These bags come flat packed, so there is no need to wait for a skip or have to worry about regional skip prices and availability.\r\n\r\nAs well as reducing the direct costs of waste management, we can improve operational efficiencies and minimise disruption and distractions to your core activities. A typical sized homes project produces 2-5 cubic yards of waste from kitchen units, bathroom suites, and central heating systems. HIPPOBAGs, from the 1 cubic yard MIDIBAG to the 4.5 yard MIGHTYBAG, are ideal for the disposal of these waste streams. MEGABAGs were designed to hold a bathroom suite and a single MIGHTYBAG has the capacity to hold both a bathroom suite and a medium kitchen.','Housing and Renovation','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 10:52:08','2015-03-13 10:52:08','',11,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(272,2,'2015-03-13 10:52:43','2015-03-13 10:52:43','The MIGHTYBAG (aka the HIPPOSKIP) was designed with kitchen and large bathroom installations in mind. The 4.5 cubic yard bag is ideal for light, bulky waste, and can easily accommodate the waste created by a standard kitchen installation. In fact, our customers find that 78% of all kitchen installations fit into a single MIGHTYBAG. For bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG will contain a complete bathroom suite, making it the perfect solution for getting rid of waste in one simple operation.\r\n\r\nAll HIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so can easily be stored until needed. In addition, the flexible sides of our bags mean that no void space is created, saving valuable room around your project. The use of a MIGHTYBAG means you pay for an average of 4.77 yds of waste per job, compared with 5.5 – 6 yards in a rigid skip. By using HIPPOWASTE you will be able to save money as well time, benefiting from the most convenient waste solution on the market.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO\'s flexible courier service, there is no need to wait for the arrival or collection of skips, meaning that you can just get on with the job and arrange a collection at a convenient time for you.\r\n\r\nOur customers often save as much as <strong>£70 on each rip-out</strong>. It might not sound a lot – but if you were to do 5,000 installations a year paying the industry standard cost of £175 to dispose of your waste, that would be <strong>a saving of £350,000, or 40%!</strong> At 15,000 installations a year, then that saving rises to <strong>saving of £1,050,000.</strong>','Installation','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 10:52:43','2015-03-13 10:52:43','',12,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/12-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(273,2,'2015-03-13 10:54:53','2015-03-13 10:54:53','<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-140 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>Galliford Try used the HIPPOBAG system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h3>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h3>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\">\r\n</a>\r\n[/quote]','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 10:54:53','2015-03-13 10:54:53','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(274,2,'2015-03-13 10:56:45','2015-03-13 10:56:45','HIPPO is a national provider of innovative and integrated waste logistics solutions, the HIPPOWASTE service caters to the needs of building and construction professionals for their waste<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-185 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/all-bags-300x212.png\" alt=\"all bags\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" /> removal.\r\n\r\nDriven by the desire to provide an affordable, convenient and reliable waste logistics service for your business, HIPPOWASTE use our innovative yellow HIPPOBAG. These large, strong and convenient skip alternatives are bought flat-packed from either our website or our trusted retailers and can be used at a time of your convenience. Once your HIPPOBAG is full, our expert couriers will take it off your hands and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPO take our environmental responsibilities very seriously, recycling 90% of the waste that we collect. In addition, our strong reputation for delivering high standards of customer care in a niche area of the waste logistics market has meant we have experienced significant growth in just seven years of trading.\r\n<h2>Here to Clear</h2>\r\nFor smaller waste logistics needs, HIPPO’s Here to Clear van is ideal. This service is especially suited to areas where access is restricted to waste and where it needs to be manually cleared.\r\n\r\nThese vans carry two of our HIPPO employees, who will ensure that your waste logistics process is carried out seamlessly.  We use a Ford Transit Tipper van for this service, which is able to hold up to 14 yards - or a tonne - of waste. Using this service incurs an additional charge.\r\n<h2>HIPPOPRO</h2>\r\nHIPPOPRO is our service for professional tradesmen, providing the essential tool for your trade. We are trusted by tradesmen around the UK to deliver a reliable, affordable and simple service to dispose of your excess waste.\r\n\r\nYou can save space and money by choosing the right sized HIPPOBAG for your business needs, from the 1 yard MIDIBAG, to the 1.5 yard MEGABAG and 4.5 yard HIPPOSKIP. Avoid cluttering up your customers’ driveways with unsightly skips and instead place neat, professional looking HIPPOBAGS at a convenient place for you.\r\n\r\nAs a tradesman you can also enjoy a saving of at least 5% on waste disposal every time that you make a collection with HIPPOPRO.\r\n<h2>Careers at HIPPO</h2>\r\nWe at HIPPO are always on the look out for new people to join our team. If you think you have the skills required to become part of our thriving waste logistics business, then we may well have a space for you at HIPPO.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About HIPPO','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 10:56:45','2015-03-13 10:56:45','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(275,2,'2015-03-13 10:59:07','2015-03-13 10:59:07','If you have any questions or queries about HIPPOWASTE, we’d love to hear from you!\r\n\r\nYou can get in touch with us via email or phone:\r\nBook Collection: 0345 850 0 850\r\n(Lines Open 08:00 until 18:00 Monday – Friday excluding Bank Holidays)\r\nEmail: sales@hippowaste.co.uk\r\n\r\nIf you are a domestic or DIY customer and are looking for information relating to local stockists or buying your HIPPOBAGS online then please visit our newly developed retail website – hippobag.co.uk\r\n\r\nLet us work with you to design the waste solution that fits your needs and saves you time and money. Enter your contact information below and one of our dedicated Account Managers will call to discuss your project.\r\n\r\nHead Office: HIPPO, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth, Hampshire, PO6 3EN','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 10:59:07','2015-03-13 10:59:07','',35,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/35-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(285,2,'2015-03-13 12:23:27','2015-03-13 12:23:27','<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-140 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"INSTALLATIONS2\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" />Galliford Try used the HIPPOBAG system for disposing of the waste generated from a major refurbishment project of a building that was being converted into student accommodation. This meant creating a lot of small rooms using plasterboard.\r\n\r\nWith the aid of pallet trucks, Galliford Try were able to manoeuvre HIPPOBAGs within confined spaces to position them close to where work was being carried out. Once full, the timely collection guarded against double-handling of waste and the subsequent downtime usually associated with waiting for a skip to be delivered and collected.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, plasterboard was recently reclassified as a non-inert waste that now needs to be disposed of separately at landfill at an increased cost. Different to traditional containers for waste, the HIPPOBAGs made it easier for the team on site to segregate the plasterboard from other waste materials so that it could be recycled, rather than sent to landfill.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h3>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h3>\r\n<em>\"The HIPPOBAG has not only provided Galliford Try with enhanced operational efficiences on site but also the ultimate solution for the segregation and subsequent recycling of plasterboard.\"</em>\r\n\r\nTerry O\'Neil, Site Manager, Galliford Try<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/INSTALLATIONS2.jpg\">\r\n</a>\r\n[/quote]','Plasterboard Recycling with Galliford Try','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 12:23:27','2015-03-13 12:23:27','',30,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(278,2,'2015-03-13 11:51:45','2015-03-13 11:51:45','Choosing a waste logistics company is a vital decision. Not only do you need a service that’s professional, affordable and environmentally responsible; you require a solution that takes care of everything from collection to disposal, so you’re free to focus on your project.\r\n\r\nWhen you choose HIPPOWASTE you know you will benefit from:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>a nationwide network for rapid collection</li>\r\n	<li>competitive pricing and market leading service</li>\r\n	<li>over 90% of your waste being recycled</li>\r\n	<li>valuable time and space saved on site, as you only use the space you need</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAt HIPPO, we provide bespoke and reliable waste solutions that help you reduce costs, save time, and meet your environmental responsibilities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Construction Waste</h2>\r\nThe construction industry is the single largest producer of waste in the UK, generating some 120 million tonnes of waste annually. We understand that a variety of waste can be produced in construction tasks, and ensure that even hazardous waste and plasterboard are dealt with responsibly and efficiently in our waste logistics projects.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO, you only have to deal with one supplier for all of your waste disposal needs, meaning that we can develop a bespoke solution for your specific challenges – giving you maximum efficiency and flexibility even in the largest of construction waste logistics tasks.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-95\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities-management-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"facilities-management-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Facilities Management</h2>\r\nUsing the HIPPOBAG to deal with heavy or bulk inert waste streams and ad hoc waste events will provide you with a number of benefits in managing waste disposal across your national or regional store estate. By working together with any existing waste contracts you have, we can assist you in reconstructing your waste services.\r\n\r\nOur service is not a regular scheduled waste collection covered by a bin contract, so you can use us for unexpected waste events whenever you need us. With thousands of HIPPOBAGS collected from store estates weekly, HIPPO provides a flexible, convenient and ethical service for your business.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"housing-rennovation-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Housing and Renovation</h2>\r\nWe have collected over half a million HIPPOBAGs from residential properties, so we understand the challenges of waste disposal in the process of improving social housing and transforming neighbourhoods.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Retail and Office Fitout</h2>\r\nDuring the refurbishment or fit out stage of retail and office premises, using a HIPPOBAG allows you to segregate waste streams on site, helping you to achieve increased recycling rates. This in return helps you to achieve your diversion from landfill objectives.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPOWASTE you’ll also benefit from the flexibility of an instant and non-bulky waste solution that is transportable and bespoke to your project. HIPPOWASTE work around your business, with our flat packed bags able to be used at any time – up to a year –after purchase, as well as being collected at a time of your convenience. This way you no-longer have to wait for skip deliveries or collections that clutter sites, hampering the progress of your workforce.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Plasterboard Recycling</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE also offer a quick and cost effective way of getting rid of plasterboard from your site or property. Through our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect. HIPPO’s environmental values mean that by using our services, you can ensure that you are disposing of your waste in a responsible and eco-friendly manner.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-97\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"installation-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Installations</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE offers an ideal service for installations. We understand the importance of minimising inconvenience to customers and their surrounding properties during a domestic remodelling. HIPPO cause the least possible disruption to your customers by ensuring that waste is kept neatly and takes up as little room as possible on site.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so don’t waste room before they are used. In addition, our reliable and flexible courier service means that you can arrange for your HIPPOBAG to be picked up at a convenient time for you. HIPPOBAGs can also be left on your – or your customer’s – property, making them far more tidy and convenient than a traditional skip that would be left on the road.\r\n\r\nFor bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG is ideal, able to hold an entire bathroom suite. The larger 4.5 Yard HIPPOSKIP was developed to accommodate kitchen and larger bathroom installation projects.','Services','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 11:51:45','2015-03-13 11:51:45','',6,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(279,2,'2015-03-13 11:55:36','2015-03-13 11:55:36','HIPPO provide waste logistics services to projects across the construction sector, including social housing, retail and internal fit-out.\r\n\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites nationwide use HIPPO because of the convenience and reliability of our lightweight and flexible HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, helping you to improve site efficiency.\r\n\r\nHIPPO can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all of your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/plasterboard-recycling/\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and achieve diversion from landfill objectives, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, giving you flexibility in collection volumes, as well as in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRead our Construction case study <a title=\"Case Study: Construction\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/case-study-three/\">here</a>.','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 11:55:36','2015-03-13 11:55:36','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(284,2,'2015-03-13 12:21:20','2015-03-13 12:21:20','Choosing a waste logistics company is a vital decision. Not only do you need a service that’s professional, affordable and environmentally responsible; you require a solution that takes care of everything from collection to disposal, so you’re free to focus on your project.\r\n\r\nWhen you choose HIPPOWASTE you know you will benefit from:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>a nationwide network for rapid collection</li>\r\n	<li>competitive pricing and market leading service</li>\r\n	<li>over 90% of your waste being recycled</li>\r\n	<li>valuable time and space saved on site, as you only use the space you need</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAt HIPPO, we provide bespoke and reliable waste solutions that help you reduce costs, save time, and meet your environmental responsibilities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-94\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"construction-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Construction Waste</h2>\r\nThe <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/construction/\">construction industry</a> is the single largest producer of waste in the UK, generating some 120 million tonnes of waste annually. We understand that a variety of waste can be produced in construction tasks, and ensure that even hazardous waste and plasterboard are dealt with responsibly and efficiently in our waste logistics projects.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO, you only have to deal with one supplier for all of your waste disposal needs, meaning that we can develop a bespoke solution for your specific challenges – giving you maximum efficiency and flexibility even in the largest of construction waste logistics tasks.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-95\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/facilities-management-icon1-150x150.png\" alt=\"facilities-management-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Facilities Management</h2>\r\nUsing the HIPPOBAG to deal with heavy or bulk inert waste streams and ad hoc waste events will provide you with a number of benefits in managing waste disposal across your national or regional store estate. By working together with any existing waste contracts you have, we can assist you in <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/facilities-management/\">reconstructing your waste services</a>.\r\n\r\nOur service is not a regular scheduled waste collection covered by a bin contract, so you can use us for unexpected waste events whenever you need us. With thousands of HIPPOBAGS collected from store estates weekly, HIPPO provides a flexible, convenient and ethical service for your business.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/housing-rennovation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"housing-rennovation-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Housing and Renovation</h2>\r\nWe have collected over half a million HIPPOBAGs from residential properties, so we understand the challenges of waste disposal in the process of improving <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/housing-and-renovation/\">social housing and transforming neighbourhoods</a>.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-99\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-offices-fitout-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"retail-offices-fitout-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Retail and Office Fitout</h2>\r\nDuring the <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/retail-and-offices-fitout/\">refurbishment or fit out stage of retail and office premises</a>, using a HIPPOBAG allows you to segregate waste streams on site, helping you to achieve increased recycling rates. This in return helps you to achieve your diversion from landfill objectives.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPOWASTE you’ll also benefit from the flexibility of an instant and non-bulky waste solution that is transportable and bespoke to your project. HIPPOWASTE work around your business, with our flat packed bags able to be used at any time – up to a year –after purchase, as well as being collected at a time of your convenience. This way you no-longer have to wait for skip deliveries or collections that clutter sites, hampering the progress of your workforce.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-98\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"plasterboard-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Plasterboard Recycling</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE also offer a <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/plasterboard-recycling/\">quick and cost effective way of getting rid of plasterboard</a> from your site or property. Through our dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, we recycle 100% of uncontaminated plasterboard that we collect. HIPPO’s environmental values mean that by using our services, you can ensure that you are disposing of your waste in a responsible and eco-friendly manner.\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-97\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installation-icon-150x150.png\" alt=\"installation-icon\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" /> Installations</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE offers an <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/installation/\">ideal service for installations</a>. We understand the importance of minimising inconvenience to customers and their surrounding properties during a domestic remodelling. HIPPO cause the least possible disruption to your customers by ensuring that waste is kept neatly and takes up as little room as possible on site.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so don’t waste room before they are used. In addition, our reliable and flexible courier service means that you can arrange for your HIPPOBAG to be picked up at a convenient time for you. HIPPOBAGs can also be left on your – or your customer’s – property, making them far more tidy and convenient than a traditional skip that would be left on the road.\r\n\r\nFor bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG is ideal, able to hold an entire bathroom suite. The larger 4.5 Yard HIPPOSKIP was developed to accommodate kitchen and larger bathroom installation projects.','Services','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 12:21:20','2015-03-13 12:21:20','',6,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(375,2,'2015-03-16 10:28:39','2015-03-16 10:28:39','','about-hippo','','inherit','open','open','','about-hippo-2','','','2015-03-16 10:28:53','2015-03-16 10:28:53','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/about-hippo1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(353,2,'2015-03-14 09:37:15','2015-03-14 09:37:15','<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-185 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/all-bags-300x212.png\" alt=\"all bags\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" />HIPPO is a national provider of innovative and integrated waste logistics solutions, the HIPPOWASTE service caters to the needs of building and construction professionals for their waste removal.\r\n\r\nDriven by the desire to provide an affordable, convenient and reliable waste logistics service for your business, HIPPOWASTE use our innovative yellow HIPPOBAG. These large, strong and convenient skip alternatives are bought flat-packed from either our website or our trusted retailers and can be used at a time of your convenience. Once your HIPPOBAG is full, our expert couriers will take it off your hands and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPO take our environmental responsibilities very seriously, recycling 90% of the waste that we collect. In addition, our strong reputation for delivering high standards of customer care in a niche area of the waste logistics market has meant we have experienced significant growth in just seven years of trading.\r\n<h2>Here to Clear</h2>\r\nFor smaller waste logistics needs, HIPPO’s Here to Clear van is ideal. This service is especially suited to areas where access is restricted to waste and where it needs to be manually cleared.\r\n\r\nThese vans carry two of our HIPPO employees, who will ensure that your waste logistics process is carried out seamlessly.  We use a Ford Transit Tipper van for this service, which is able to hold up to 14 yards - or a tonne - of waste. Using this service incurs an additional charge.\r\n<h2>HIPPOPRO</h2>\r\nHIPPOPRO is our service for professional tradesmen, providing the essential tool for your trade. We are trusted by tradesmen around the UK to deliver a reliable, affordable and simple service to dispose of your excess waste.\r\n\r\nYou can save space and money by choosing the right sized HIPPOBAG for your business needs, from the 1 yard MIDIBAG, to the 1.5 yard MEGABAG and 4.5 yard HIPPOSKIP. Avoid cluttering up your customers’ driveways with unsightly skips and instead place neat, professional looking HIPPOBAGS at a convenient place for you.\r\n\r\nAs a tradesman you can also enjoy a saving of at least 5% on waste disposal every time that you make a collection with HIPPOPRO.\r\n<h2>Careers at HIPPO</h2>\r\nWe at HIPPO are always <a title=\"Careers at HIPPOWASTE\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/about/careers-at-hippowaste/\">on the look out for new people to join our team</a>. If you think you have the skills required to become part of our thriving waste logistics business, then we may well have a space for you at HIPPO.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-314 size-full\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/about-hippo.jpg\" alt=\"About Hippo\" width=\"997\" height=\"399\" />','About HIPPO','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2015-03-14 09:37:15','2015-03-14 09:37:15','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(315,2,'2015-03-13 16:52:42','2015-03-13 16:52:42','<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-314 size-full\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/about-hippo.jpg\" alt=\"About Hippo\" width=\"997\" height=\"399\" />\r\n\r\nHIPPO is a national provider of innovative and integrated waste logistics solutions, the HIPPOWASTE service caters to the needs of building and construction professionals for their waste removal.\r\n\r\nDriven by the desire to provide an affordable, convenient and reliable waste logistics service for your business, HIPPOWASTE use our innovative yellow HIPPOBAG. These large, strong and convenient skip alternatives are bought flat-packed from either our website or our trusted retailers and can be used at a time of your convenience. Once your HIPPOBAG is full, our expert couriers will take it off your hands and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPO take our environmental responsibilities very seriously, recycling 90% of the waste that we collect. In addition, our strong reputation for delivering high standards of customer care in a niche area of the waste logistics market has meant we have experienced significant growth in just seven years of trading.\r\n<h2>Here to Clear</h2>\r\nFor smaller waste logistics needs, HIPPO’s Here to Clear van is ideal. This service is especially suited to areas where access is restricted to waste and where it needs to be manually cleared.\r\n\r\nThese vans carry two of our HIPPO employees, who will ensure that your waste logistics process is carried out seamlessly.  We use a Ford Transit Tipper van for this service, which is able to hold up to 14 yards - or a tonne - of waste. Using this service incurs an additional charge.\r\n<h2>HIPPOPRO</h2>\r\nHIPPOPRO is our service for professional tradesmen, providing the essential tool for your trade. We are trusted by tradesmen around the UK to deliver a reliable, affordable and simple service to dispose of your excess waste.<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-185 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/all-bags-300x212.png\" alt=\"all bags\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" />\r\n\r\nYou can save space and money by choosing the right sized HIPPOBAG for your business needs, from the 1 yard MIDIBAG, to the 1.5 yard MEGABAG and 4.5 yard HIPPOSKIP. Avoid cluttering up your customers’ driveways with unsightly skips and instead place neat, professional looking HIPPOBAGS at a convenient place for you.\r\n\r\nAs a tradesman you can also enjoy a saving of at least 5% on waste disposal every time that you make a collection with HIPPOPRO.\r\n<h2>Careers at HIPPO</h2>\r\nWe at HIPPO are always <a title=\"Careers at HIPPOWASTE\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/about/careers-at-hippowaste/\">on the look out for new people to join our team</a>. If you think you have the skills required to become part of our thriving waste logistics business, then we may well have a space for you at HIPPO.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About HIPPO','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 16:52:42','2015-03-13 16:52:42','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(333,2,'2015-03-13 18:44:02','2015-03-13 18:44:02','<h2>HIPPO provide waste logistics services to projects across the construction sector, including social housing, retail and internal fit-out.</h2>\r\n\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites nationwide use HIPPO because of the convenience and reliability of our lightweight and flexible HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, helping you to improve site efficiency.\r\n\r\nHIPPO can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all of your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/plasterboard-recycling/\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and achieve diversion from landfill objectives, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, giving you flexibility in collection volumes, as well as in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/construction-case-study/\">Read our Construction case study here</a>.','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 18:44:02','2015-03-13 18:44:02','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(288,2,'2015-03-13 12:26:32','2015-03-13 12:26:32','To protect your privacy we provide this notice explaining our online information practices and the choices you can make about the way your information is collected and used.\r\n\r\n1. The information we collect\r\n\r\nThis notice applies to all information collected or submitted on this website. You can purchase products which require you to enter personal information. The types of personal information collected on these pages are:\r\n\r\nName\r\nE-mail address\r\nPostal address\r\nTelephone/mobile number\r\n2. The way we use information\r\n\r\nWe use return e-mail addresses to answer the e-mails we receive. If you request a call back we will use the telephone details provided. If there is a problem with your order we will either telephone or email you to communicate that information with you. The information is not used for any other purpose and is not shared with outside parties.\r\n\r\n3. Email marketing and opt-out\r\n\r\nUpon making a purchase you can opt in to receive reminders about using your HIPPOBAG and also occasional emails containing useful information and promotions from HIPPOBAG. These emails frequent approximately four per year. And you can opt out at anytime by clicking the ‘unsubscribe’ link contained within the email or by emailing info@hippowaste.co.uk.\r\n\r\n4. Our commitment to data security\r\n\r\nWe never use or share the personally identifiable information provided to us online in ways unrelated to those described above without also providing an opportunity for you to opt out or otherwise prohibit such unrelated uses. It will never be supplied to anyone outside HIPPO without first obtaining your consent, unless we are obliged to disclose it by law. To prevent unauthorised access, maintain data accuracy and ensure the correct use of information, we have put in place appropriate physical, electronic and managerial procedures to safeguard and secure the information we collect online. We will ensure that all personal information supplied is held securely, in accordance with the Data Protection Act 1998.\r\n\r\n5. Credit / debit card information\r\n\r\nAll payment information is processed by HSBC Merchant Services and all internet transactions are secured by Verified by Visa and MasterCard SecureCode. Card information is taken over an SSL encrypted server verified by VeriSign. HIPPO do not store or retain any banking information once a payment has been processed.\r\n\r\n6. Cookies\r\n\r\nWe may use \'cookies\' for administrative purposes such as cataloguing traffic patterns throughout the website and can use a cookie to assign a \'user ID\' for this purpose. Cookies, by themselves, cannot be used to find out the identity of any user. If you have a user ID this will automatically identify your computer - but not you - to our server when you visit our website. Unless you specifically tell us, we will never know who you are, even if we do assign a cookie to your computer.\r\n\r\n7. Users under 18\r\n\r\nIf you are under 18, please obtain your parent/guardian\'s permission beforehand whenever you provide personal information to HIPPO\'s website. Users without this consent are not allowed to provide us with personal information.\r\n\r\n8. Display ads and remarketing\r\n\r\nOn this website we may use display adverts and retargeting adverts which are used to advertise our products and service online.\r\n\r\nThird party vendors including Google will show adverts on sites across the internet.  To opt out or alter your settings click here Ads Preferences Manager\r\n\r\nWe (hippowaste.co.uk) and third-party vendors, including Google, use first-party cookies (such as the Google Analytics cookie) and third-party cookies (such as the DoubleClick cookie) together to inform, optimize, and serve ads based on someone\'s past visits to your website.','Terms & Conditions','','inherit','open','open','','227-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 12:26:32','2015-03-13 12:26:32','',227,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/227-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(289,2,'2015-03-13 12:27:10','2015-03-13 12:27:10','To protect your privacy we provide this notice explaining our online information practices and the choices you can make about the way your information is collected and used.\r\n\r\n1. The information we collect\r\n\r\nThis notice applies to all information collected or submitted on this website. You can purchase products which require you to enter personal information. The types of personal information collected on these pages are:\r\n\r\nName\r\nE-mail address\r\nPostal address\r\nTelephone/mobile number\r\n2. The way we use information\r\n\r\nWe use return e-mail addresses to answer the e-mails we receive. If you request a call back we will use the telephone details provided. If there is a problem with your order we will either telephone or email you to communicate that information with you. The information is not used for any other purpose and is not shared with outside parties.\r\n\r\n3. Email marketing and opt-out\r\n\r\nUpon making a purchase you can opt in to receive reminders about using your HIPPOBAG and also occasional emails containing useful information and promotions from HIPPOBAG. These emails frequent approximately four per year. And you can opt out at anytime by clicking the ‘unsubscribe’ link contained within the email or by emailing info@hippowaste.co.uk.\r\n\r\n4. Our commitment to data security\r\n\r\nWe never use or share the personally identifiable information provided to us online in ways unrelated to those described above without also providing an opportunity for you to opt out or otherwise prohibit such unrelated uses. It will never be supplied to anyone outside HIPPO without first obtaining your consent, unless we are obliged to disclose it by law. To prevent unauthorised access, maintain data accuracy and ensure the correct use of information, we have put in place appropriate physical, electronic and managerial procedures to safeguard and secure the information we collect online. We will ensure that all personal information supplied is held securely, in accordance with the Data Protection Act 1998.\r\n\r\n5. Credit / debit card information\r\n\r\nAll payment information is processed by HSBC Merchant Services and all internet transactions are secured by Verified by Visa and MasterCard SecureCode. Card information is taken over an SSL encrypted server verified by VeriSign. HIPPO do not store or retain any banking information once a payment has been processed.\r\n\r\n6. Cookies\r\n\r\nWe may use \'cookies\' for administrative purposes such as cataloguing traffic patterns throughout the website and can use a cookie to assign a \'user ID\' for this purpose. Cookies, by themselves, cannot be used to find out the identity of any user. If you have a user ID this will automatically identify your computer - but not you - to our server when you visit our website. Unless you specifically tell us, we will never know who you are, even if we do assign a cookie to your computer.\r\n\r\n7. Users under 18\r\n\r\nIf you are under 18, please obtain your parent/guardian\'s permission beforehand whenever you provide personal information to HIPPO\'s website. Users without this consent are not allowed to provide us with personal information.\r\n\r\n8. Display ads and remarketing\r\n\r\nOn this website we may use display adverts and retargeting adverts which are used to advertise our products and service online.\r\n\r\nThird party vendors including Google will show adverts on sites across the internet.  To opt out or alter your settings click here Ads Preferences Manager\r\n\r\nWe (hippowaste.co.uk) and third-party vendors, including Google, use first-party cookies (such as the Google Analytics cookie) and third-party cookies (such as the DoubleClick cookie) together to inform, optimize, and serve ads based on someone\'s past visits to your website.','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','229-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 12:27:10','2015-03-13 12:27:10','',229,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/229-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(292,2,'2015-03-13 14:08:10','2015-03-13 14:08:10','The chances are, when you join us, you\'ve got more than a job in mind. You’ll be thinking about how joining HIPPO will contribute to your longer term aims – and so will we.\r\n\r\nWe work to provide opportunities for development through both training and through career development. Our training is themed around individuals’ career objectives, departmental requirements, and wider business needs or changes, making sure we’re all ready for our next challenge.\r\n\r\nWe are particularly proud of our team’s career progression – we’re not a huge organisation, but through creative thinking, an eye for talent, and the flexibility that comes with the Company’s growth and development, we have been able to spot opportunities for people to move to roles which are more senior, more challenging, or represent a change of career. This is great for us, as we retain our committed and talented people; and it allows people with talent and ambition to pursue their career aspirations. 9% of our team were promoted into their current roles, and 12% have moved to a different role during their time with HIPPO.\r\n\r\nTo apply for any of vacancies, please email your CV with a covering letter to recruitment@hippowaste.co.uk or post it to: HR Department, HIPPO, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth PO6 3EN\r\n<h2>Current Vacancies</h2>\r\nWe have no current vacancies.','Careers at HIPPOWASTE','','inherit','open','open','','34-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 14:08:10','2015-03-13 14:08:10','',34,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/34-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(293,2,'2015-03-13 15:22:59','2015-03-13 15:22:59','HIPPO is a national provider of innovative and integrated waste logistics solutions, the HIPPOWASTE service caters to the needs of building and construction professionals for their waste<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-185 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/all-bags-300x212.png\" alt=\"all bags\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" /> removal.\r\n\r\nDriven by the desire to provide an affordable, convenient and reliable waste logistics service for your business, HIPPOWASTE use our innovative yellow HIPPOBAG. These large, strong and convenient skip alternatives are bought flat-packed from either our website or our trusted retailers and can be used at a time of your convenience. Once your HIPPOBAG is full, our expert couriers will take it off your hands and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPO take our environmental responsibilities very seriously, recycling 90% of the waste that we collect. In addition, our strong reputation for delivering high standards of customer care in a niche area of the waste logistics market has meant we have experienced significant growth in just seven years of trading.\r\n<h2>Here to Clear</h2>\r\nFor smaller waste logistics needs, HIPPO’s Here to Clear van is ideal. This service is especially suited to areas where access is restricted to waste and where it needs to be manually cleared.\r\n\r\nThese vans carry two of our HIPPO employees, who will ensure that your waste logistics process is carried out seamlessly.  We use a Ford Transit Tipper van for this service, which is able to hold up to 14 yards - or a tonne - of waste. Using this service incurs an additional charge.\r\n<h2>HIPPOPRO</h2>\r\nHIPPOPRO is our service for professional tradesmen, providing the essential tool for your trade. We are trusted by tradesmen around the UK to deliver a reliable, affordable and simple service to dispose of your excess waste.\r\n\r\nYou can save space and money by choosing the right sized HIPPOBAG for your business needs, from the 1 yard MIDIBAG, to the 1.5 yard MEGABAG and 4.5 yard HIPPOSKIP. Avoid cluttering up your customers’ driveways with unsightly skips and instead place neat, professional looking HIPPOBAGS at a convenient place for you.\r\n\r\nAs a tradesman you can also enjoy a saving of at least 5% on waste disposal every time that you make a collection with HIPPOPRO.\r\n<h2>Careers at HIPPO</h2>\r\nWe at HIPPO are always <a title=\"Careers at HIPPOWASTE\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/about/careers-at-hippowaste/\">on the look out for new people to join our team</a>. If you think you have the skills required to become part of our thriving waste logistics business, then we may well have a space for you at HIPPO.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About HIPPO','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 15:22:59','2015-03-13 15:22:59','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(290,2,'2015-03-13 12:32:23','2015-03-13 12:32:23','<strong>Website Terms and Conditions:</strong>\r\n\r\nUse of this website constitutes your acceptance of these terms and conditions, which take effect immediately on your first use of the website. HIPPO reserves the right to add to or change these terms and conditions at any time by posting changes online and it is your responsibility to refer to and comply with these terms on accessing the website. Your continued use of this website after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of these terms and conditions as modified.\r\n\r\nMaterial may not be copied, reproduced, republished, downloaded, posted, broadcast or transmitted in any way except for your own personal non-commercial home use. Any other use requires the prior written permission of HIPPO. You agree not to adapt, alter or create a derivative work from any of the material contained in this website or use it for any other purpose other than for your personal non-commercial use. You agree to use this website only for lawful purposes, and in a manner that does not infringe the rights of, or restrict or inhibit the use and enjoyment of this website by any third party. Such restriction or inhibition includes, without limitation, conduct which is unlawful, or which may harass or cause distress or inconvenience to any person and the transmission of obscene or offensive content or disruption of normal flow of dialogue within this website.\r\n\r\nThe information contained on this website does not, and will not, form any part of a contract or offer for sale. Furthermore it does not constitute an offer capable of acceptance and no binding commitment may be entered into on the basis of the information contained on this website.\r\n\r\nLinks to the HIPPOWASTE website must be direct to the HIPPOWASTE homepage. HIPPO disclaims all liability for any legal or other consequences (including for infringement of third party rights) of links made to the HIPPOWASTE website.\r\n\r\nHIPPO provides the material published on its website on the basis that it disclaims all warranties in respect of such material, whether express or implied. Neither HIPPO nor the original providers of the material accept any liability for any direct, indirect, incidental or consequential loss of business, revenues or profits or special damages arising from the publication of the material on the HIPPOWASTEwebsite. The names, images and logos identifying HIPPO or third parties and their products and services are proprietary marks of HIPPO and/or third parties. Nothing contained herein shall be construed as conferring by implication, estoppel or otherwise any licence or right under any trademark or patent of HIPPO, or any other third party.\r\n\r\nHIPPO endeavours to ensure that all information and material on the website is correct and accurate but does not accept any liability for errors or omissions; neither does HIPPO warrant that use of this website will be uninterrupted or error free, that defects will be corrected, or that this website or the server that makes it available are free of viruses or bugs or represents the full functionality, accuracy, and reliability of the materials.\r\n\r\nHIPPO is not responsible for the content of any material you encounter after leaving our website via a link in it or otherwise and HIPPO excludes to the fullest extent permitted by law all liability that may arise in respect of such material.\r\n\r\nIf any of these Terms and Conditions should be determined to be illegal, invalid or otherwise unenforceable by reason of the laws of any state or country in which these Terms and Conditions are intended to be effective, then to the extent and within the jurisdiction which that Term or Condition is illegal, invalid or unenforceable, it shall be severed and deleted from this clause and the remaining terms and conditions shall survive, remain in full force and effect and continue to be binding and enforceable.\r\n\r\nThese Terms and Conditions shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of England and Wales. Disputes arising here from shall be exclusively subject to the jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.\r\n\r\nIf these terms and conditions are not accepted in full, use of this website must be terminated immediately.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cookies and Information Usage</strong>\r\n\r\nIn summary, the cookies that we track on www.hippowaste.co.uk are for Google Analytics purposes so that we can continue to build you a better website. We also use cookies for our live chat system, so that we can see that you are visiting our website and provide you with live customer support. Your right to refuse cookies and what happens if you refuse them: You can refuse cookies by activating the relevant setting on your internet browser. However, if you do so you may not be able to access all or parts of our website, such as the live chat service. If you carry on using our website and do not change your browser settings we will assume you consent to us using cookies as described above. There are two broad categories of cookies:\r\n\r\nPersistent cookies: Persistent cookies remain on your device until deleted manually or automatically.\r\nSession cookies: Session cookies remain on your device until you close your browser when they are automatically deleted.\r\nTypes of information we use\r\n\r\nUsername and password: To provide you with a user account, this includes a user name and password which we keep in case you have any log-in problems or have forgotten your username.\r\n\r\nName, address and postcode: To allow us to send the HIPPOWASTE to you at your stated address and for collection purposes.\r\n\r\nEmail address: We send confirmation of any orders you make to your given email address, we may use your email address to contact you should any issues occur with your order and if you have opted in, send you relevant marketing from time to time.\r\n\r\nTelephone number: This is to contact you directly should there be any problems with your order, collection and if you have requested a call back or to be contacted the day before your collection is taking place.\r\n\r\nPayment card number, expiry date, issue no and name of card holder: This is to process and take payment for your order.\r\n\r\nIP addresses: When you visit our site, we will automatically receive your IP address, a unique identifier for your computer or other access device. This is used to analyse and improve our website and also to communicate with your computer via our live chat service.\r\n\r\nCookies: Cookies take minimal pieces of information from your browser about which areas of the website you access. We use this information purely to improve the layout, information and customer experience of the website based on this data. Our live chat service, which runs through a service called O lark, requires cookies to see that you are currently on our website and on which page, which allows us to provide you with a better standard of live customer service.\r\n\r\n<strong>Copyright</strong>\r\n\r\nAll rights, including copyright and database right, on the HIPPOWASTE website and its contents, are owned by or licensed to HIPPO, or otherwise used by HIPPO as permitted by applicable law. In accessing the HIPPOWASTE website, you agree that you will access the contents solely for your own private use and not for any commercial or public use. You are not permitted to copy, download, store (including in any other website), distribute, transmit, broadcast, adapt or change in any way the content of these web pages without the prior written consent of HIPPO or in accordance with the Copyright, Designs and Patents Act 1988.','Terms & Conditions','','inherit','open','open','','227-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 12:32:23','2015-03-13 12:32:23','',227,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/227-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(376,2,'2015-06-15 11:08:57','2015-06-15 10:08:57','<img class=\" size-medium wp-image-185 alignright\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/all-bags-300x212.png\" alt=\"all bags\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" />HIPPO is a national provider of innovative and integrated waste logistics solutions. The HIPPO service caters to the waste removal needs of a <a title=\"Business Solutions\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/business-solutions/\">huge range of industries</a>, from facilities management to building and construction (with everything in between!).\n\nDriven by the desire to provide an affordable, convenient and reliable waste logistics service for your business, HIPPO uses innovative yellow HIPPOBAGs. These large, strong and convenient skip alternatives are ideal . Once your HIPPOBAG is full, our expert drivers will take it off your hands and dispose of it responsibly.\n\nHIPPO take our environmental responsibilities very seriously, recycling 90% of the waste that we collect. In addition, our strong reputation for delivering high standards of customer care in a niche area of the waste logistics market has meant we have experienced significant growth over our years of trading.\n<h2>Here to Clear</h2>\nFor smaller waste logistics needs, HIPPO’s Here to Clear van is ideal. This service is especially suited to areas where access is restricted to waste and where it needs to be manually cleared.\n\nThese vans carry two of our HIPPO employees, who will ensure that your waste logistics process is carried out seamlessly.  We use a Tipper van for this service, which is able to hold up to 14 yards - or a tonne - of waste.\n<h2>HIPPOTRADE</h2>\nHIPPOTRADE is our service for professional tradesmen, providing the essential tool for your trade. We are trusted by tradesmen around the UK to deliver a reliable, affordable and simple service to dispose of your excess waste.\n\nYou can save space and money by choosing the right sized HIPPOBAG for your business needs, from the 1 yard MIDIBAG, to the 1.5 yard MEGABAG and 4.5 yard HIPPOSKIP. Avoid cluttering up your customers’ driveways with unsightly skips and instead place neat, professional looking HIPPOBAGs at a convenient place for you.\n\nAs a tradesman you can also enjoy discounted rates on waste disposal every time that you make a collection with HIPPOPRO.\n<h2>Careers at HIPPO</h2>\nWe at HIPPO are always <a title=\"Careers at HIPPOWASTE\" href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/about/careers-at-hippowaste/\">on the look out for new people to join our team</a>. If you think you have the skills required to become part of our thriving waste logistics business, then we may well have a space for you at HIPPO.\n\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/about-hippo1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-375 size-full\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/about-hippo1.jpg\" alt=\"about HIPPO\" width=\"1015\" height=\"410\" /></a>','About HIPPO','','inherit','open','open','','8-autosave-v1','','','2015-06-15 11:08:57','2015-06-15 10:08:57','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/8-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(314,2,'2015-03-13 16:50:35','2015-03-13 16:50:35','','about-hippo','','inherit','open','open','','about-hippo','','','2015-03-13 16:50:35','2015-03-13 16:50:35','',8,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/about-hippo.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(316,2,'2015-03-13 17:17:39','2015-03-13 17:17:39','','about-hippowaste','','inherit','open','open','','about-hippowaste','','','2015-03-13 17:17:55','2015-03-13 17:17:55','',33,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/about-hippowaste.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(317,2,'2015-03-13 17:18:46','2015-03-13 17:18:46','<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/about-hippowaste.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-316\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/about-hippowaste.jpg\" alt=\"About HIPPOWASTE\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" /></a>Why Choose HIPPO?</h2>\r\nSelecting a waste logistics service is a vital decision for any business. HIPPOWASTE provide a reliable, affordable and convenient national skip alternative for any sized business. Our innovative HIPPOBAG comes in three convenient sizes and is available either online or from our trusted stockists around the UK.\r\n\r\nA HIPPOBAG is the perfect alternative to traditional skip hire for a number of reasons; a HIPPOBAG is bought flat packed and can be used at a convenient time for you, where you would have a limited time if you hired a skip. When you are finished with your HIPPOBAG, simply arrange a collection and our professional couriers will collect your waste and dispose of it responsibly.\r\n\r\nHIPPOBAGs also take up very little space, and you can suit the size of bag to the specific needs of your project; this means you don’t need to pay the full price that you would for a skip if your needs are smaller. You can also segregate waste into different streams using HIPPOBAGs, allowing you to increase recycling rates.\r\n\r\nHIPPO’s environmental policies mean you can rest assured that your waste is being handled and disposed of in a responsible manner. We typically recycle around 90% of the waste that we collect. HIPPO are also committed to excellent customer service and have an average customer review rating of 4.7 out of 5.\r\n<h2>Our Waste Logistics Experts</h2>\r\nHIPPOWASTE provide waste logistics services for a huge variety of projects. Whether you require waste logistics in new build and construction, housing and renovation, facilities management, kitchen and bathroom installation, retail and office fit out or virtually any waste-producing project; HIPPO offer the ideal service for your needs.\r\n\r\nHIPPOWASTE also run a dedicated plasterboard disposal and recycling scheme, where we collect uncontaminated plasterboard and recycle 100% of it.\r\n\r\nWith HIPPO’s trusted, flexible and project–specific approach, we can suit our services perfectly to your waste logistics needs, whilst ensuring that you receive value for money and  that your waste is dealt with responsibly.','About HIPPOWASTE','','inherit','open','open','','33-revision-v1','','','2015-03-13 17:18:46','2015-03-13 17:18:46','',33,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/33-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(318,2,'2015-03-13 17:20:48','2015-03-13 17:20:48','','PBWPIX','','inherit','open','open','','pbwpix','','','2015-03-13 17:21:02','2015-03-13 17:21:02','',34,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/careers.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(405,2,'2015-06-01 11:31:41','2015-06-01 10:31:41','<img class=\"alignright wp-image-321\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/careers1.jpg\" alt=\"careers\" width=\"455\" height=\"410\" />The chances are when you join us, you\'ll have more than a job in mind. You’ll be thinking about how joining HIPPO will contribute to your longer term aims – and so will we.\n<h2>opportunities</h2>\nWe work to provide opportunities for development through both training and through career development. Our training is themed around individuals’ career objectives, departmental requirements, and wider business needs or changes, making sure we’re all ready for our next challenge.\n<h2>progression</h2>\nWe are particularly proud of our team’s career progression – we’re not a huge organisation, but through creative thinking, an eye for talent, and the flexibility that comes with the Company’s growth and development, we have been able to spot opportunities for people to move to roles which are more senior, more challenging, or represent a change of career. This is great for us, as we retain our committed and talented people - and it allows people with talent and ambition to pursue their career aspirations. 9% of our team were promoted into their current roles, and 12% have moved to a different role during their time with HIPPO.\n<h2>how to apply</h2>\nTo apply for any of vacancies, please email your CV with a covering letter to recruitment@hippowaste.co.uk or post it to: HR Department, HIPPO, 1000 Lakeside, North Harbour, Portsmouth PO6 3EN\n<h2>Current Vacancies</h2>\nWe have no current vacancies.','Careers at HIPPOWASTE','','inherit','open','open','','34-autosave-v1','','','2015-06-01 11:31:41','2015-06-01 10:31:41','',34,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/34-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(321,2,'2015-03-13 17:41:02','2015-03-13 17:41:02','','careers','','inherit'