open','','construction2-2','','','2015-04-07 14:32:09','2015-04-07 13:32:09','',12,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction21.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(455,2,'2015-04-07 13:56:19','2015-04-07 12:56:19','<h2>HIPPO Provide Waste Logistics Services to Projects Across the Construction Sector</h2>\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n<h2>Flexibile</h2>\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites nationwide use HIPPO because of the convenience and reliability of our lightweight and flexible HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, helping you to improve site efficiency.\r\n<h2>Ethical</h2>\r\nHIPPO can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all of your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/plasterboard-recycling/\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n<h2>Bespoke</h2>\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and achieve diversion from landfill objectives, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, giving you flexibility in collection volumes, as well as in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/construction-case-study/\">Read our Construction case study here</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction22.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-452\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction22.jpg\" alt=\"construction HIPPO\" width=\"1015\" height=\"489\" /></a>','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-04-07 13:56:19','2015-04-07 12:56:19','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(452,2,'2015-04-07 13:40:07','2015-04-07 12:40:07','','construction-hippo','','inherit','open','open','','construction2','','','2015-04-07 13:40:25','2015-04-07 12:40:25','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction22.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(453,2,'2015-04-07 13:40:31','2015-04-07 12:40:31','<h2>HIPPO Provide Waste Logistics Services to Projects Across the Construction Sector</h2>\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n<h2>Flexibile</h2>\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites nationwide use HIPPO because of the convenience and reliability of our lightweight and flexible HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, helping you to improve site efficiency.\r\n<h2>Ethical</h2>\r\nHIPPO can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all of your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/plasterboard-recycling/\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n<h2>Bespoke</h2>\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and achieve diversion from landfill objectives, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, giving you flexibility in collection volumes, as well as in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/construction-case-study/\">Read our Construction case study here</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction22.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-452 size-full\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction22.jpg\" alt=\"construction HIPPO\" width=\"830\" height=\"400\" /></a>','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-04-07 13:40:31','2015-04-07 12:40:31','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(454,2,'2015-04-07 13:41:03','2015-04-07 12:41:03','<h2>HIPPO Provide Waste Logistics Services to Projects Across the Construction Sector</h2>\r\nFrom helping you plan the volume and types of waste you’ll encounter, to knowing where your waste is going and what level of recycling you can achieve, HIPPO works with you from start to finish to help to deliver your project efficiently. What’s more, our national transport infrastructure means wherever you are, you will receive a reliable collection service that you can trust.\r\n<h2>Flexibile</h2>\r\nThe flexibility of HIPPOBAGs allow for easy waste collection from tight, restricted sites. In addition, our national service means we can offer you a solution wherever you are in the country.\r\n\r\nConstruction sites nationwide use HIPPO because of the convenience and reliability of our lightweight and flexible HIPPOBAGs, as well as our excellent customer service. Collections can be made from different areas on large sites, including from scaffolding or loading bays, helping you to improve site efficiency.\r\n<h2>Ethical</h2>\r\nHIPPO can also ensure that you only have one supplier for all of your site waste needs, including hazardous waste and <a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/services/plasterboard-recycling/\">plasterboard</a>. We recycle around 90 per cent of the waste that we collect, so you can rest assured that your operation will be carried out ethically and responsibly.\r\n<h2>Bespoke</h2>\r\nDifferent bag sizes make it easy to segregate waste streams and achieve diversion from landfill objectives, whilst a variety of size options mean that you only ever pay for what you need, as well as saving space on site. HIPPO offer bespoke solutions developed for each site, giving you flexibility in collection volumes, as well as in the time or date of collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/construction-case-study/\">Read our Construction case study here</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction22.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-452 size-full alignleft\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction22.jpg\" alt=\"construction HIPPO\" width=\"830\" height=\"400\" /></a>','Construction','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-04-07 13:41:03','2015-04-07 12:41:03','',10,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(458,2,'2015-06-05 15:58:02','2015-06-05 14:58:02','<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-392\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/plasterboard.jpg\" alt=\"installation HIPPO\" width=\"400\" height=\"553\" /></a>HIPPO Provides Waste Logistics Services to Kitchen and Bathroom Installers</h2>\r\nThe MIGHTYBAG (aka the HIPPOSKIP) was designed with kitchen and large bathroom installations in mind. The 4.5 cubic yard bag is ideal for light, bulky waste, and can easily accommodate the waste created by a standard kitchen installation. In fact, our customers find that 90% of all kitchen installations fit into a single MIGHTYBAG. For bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG will contain a complete bathroom suite, making it the perfect solution for getting rid of waste in one simple operation.\r\n<h2>flat packed</h2>\r\nAll HIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so can easily be stored until needed. In addition, the flexible sides of our bags mean that no void space is created, saving valuable room around your project, and meaning you don\'t pay for wasted space. By using HIPPO you will be able to save money as well time, benefiting from the most convenient waste solution on the market.\r\n<h2>flexible</h2>\r\nWith HIPPO\'s flexible courier service, there is no need to wait for the arrival or collection of skips, meaning that you can just get on with the job and arrange a collection at a convenient time for you.\r\n<h2></h2>','Installation','','inherit','open','open','','12-autosave-v1','','','2015-06-05 15:58:02','2015-06-05 14:58:02','',12,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/12-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(459,2,'2015-04-07 14:07:21','2015-04-07 13:07:21','<h2>HIPPO Provide Waste Logistics Services to Kitchen and Bathroom Installers</h2>\r\nThe MIGHTYBAG (aka the HIPPOSKIP) was designed with kitchen and large bathroom installations in mind. The 4.5 cubic yard bag is ideal for light, bulky waste, and can easily accommodate the waste created by a standard kitchen installation. In fact, our customers find that 78% of all kitchen installations fit into a single MIGHTYBAG. For bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG will contain a complete bathroom suite, making it the perfect solution for getting rid of waste in one simple operation.\r\n<h2>flat packed</h2>\r\nAll HIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so can easily be stored until needed. In addition, the flexible sides of our bags mean that no void space is created, saving valuable room around your project. The use of a MIGHTYBAG means you pay for an average of 4.77 yds of waste per job, compared with 5.5 – 6 yards in a rigid skip. By using HIPPOWASTE you will be able to save money as well time, benefiting from the most convenient waste solution on the market.\r\n<h2>flexible</h2>\r\nWith HIPPO\'s flexible courier service, there is no need to wait for the arrival or collection of skips, meaning that you can just get on with the job and arrange a collection at a convenient time for you.\r\n<h2>savings</h2>\r\nOur customers often save as much as <strong>£70 on each rip-out</strong>. It might not sound a lot – but if you were to do 5,000 installations a year paying the industry standard cost of £175 to dispose of your waste, that would be <strong>a saving of £350,000, or 40%!</strong> At 15,000 installations a year, then that saving rises to <strong>saving of £1,050,000.</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installations2.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-456 size-full alignleft\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/installations2.jpg\" alt=\"installations HIPPO\" width=\"1015\" height=\"459\" /></a>','Installation','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2015-04-07 14:07:21','2015-04-07 13:07:21','',12,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/12-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(461,2,'2015-04-07 14:13:51','2015-04-07 13:13:51','<h2>HIPPO Provide Waste Logistics Services to Kitchen and Bathroom Installers</h2>\r\nThe MIGHTYBAG (aka the HIPPOSKIP) was designed with kitchen and large bathroom installations in mind. The 4.5 cubic yard bag is ideal for light, bulky waste, and can easily accommodate the waste created by a standard kitchen installation. In fact, our customers find that 78% of all kitchen installations fit into a single MIGHTYBAG. For bathroom installations, the 1.5 cubic yard MEGABAG will contain a complete bathroom suite, making it the perfect solution for getting rid of waste in one simple operation.\r\n<h2>flat packed</h2>\r\nAll HIPPOBAGs come flat packed, so can easily be stored until needed. In addition, the flexible sides of our bags mean that no void space is created, saving valuable room around your project. The use of a MIGHTYBAG means you pay for an average of 4.77 yds of waste per job, compared with 5.5 – 6 yards in a rigid skip. By using HIPPOWASTE you will be able to save money as well time, benefiting from the most convenient waste solution on the market.\r\n<h2>flexible</h2>\r\nWith HIPPO\'s flexible courier service, there is no need to wait for the arrival or collection of skips, meaning that you can just get on with the job and arrange a collection at a convenient time for you.\r\n<h2>savings</h2>\r\nOur customers often save as much as <strong>£70 on each rip-out</strong>. It might not sound a lot – but if you were to do 5,000 installations a year paying the industry standard cost of £175 to dispose of your waste, that would be <strong>a saving of £350,000, or 40%!</strong> At 15,000 installations a year, then that saving rises to <strong>saving of £1,050,000.</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction23.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-460 size-full\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/construction23.jpg\" alt=\"installations HIPPO\" width=\"1015\" height=\"459\" /></a>','Installation','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2015-04-07 14:13:51','2015-04-07 13:13:51','',12,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/12-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(466,2,'2015-04-07 14:39:12','2015-04-07 13:39:12','<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-casestudy-e1426505179570.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-398\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-casestudy-e1426505179570.jpg\" alt=\"facilities HIPPO\" width=\"369\" height=\"549\" /></a>HIPPO Provide Waste Logistics Services to Retail and Office Fit-out Projects</h2>\r\nHIPPO offer an effective service for use during the refurbishment or fit-out stage of retail and office premises.\r\n\r\nUsing a HIPPOBAG allows you to segregate waste streams on site, making it easy for you to increase your recycling rates, in turn helping you to achieve your diversion from landfill objectives.\r\n<h2>Efficient</h2>\r\nHIPPOBAGs are a waste logistics solution without the space or time restrictions that you will encounter when either buying a skip or handling waste logistics yourself. With the efficiencies in time and space that are delivered by HIPPOWASTE, your workforce will be more productive and your business will save money.\r\n<h2>flexible</h2>\r\nHIPPO offer an affordable, flexible and instant waste solution that is both transportable and bespoke to your project. In addition, HIPPOBAGs allow you to carry out the work at a suitable time for you, rather than when you are able to hire a skip. This way you can take greater control of your waste logistics operation and avoid unnecessary hassle during your retail or office fit out project.\r\n<h2>3 different sizes</h2>\r\nHIPPO’s strong, non-bulky skip alternatives come in three different sizes, so you can match the size of the HIPPOBAG you purchase to the size of the project you are undertaking, meaning that you will never pay for more than you need and will save valuable space around your project.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/retail-case-study/\">Read our retail and office fit-out case study here</a>.','Retail and Office Fit-out','','inherit','open','open','','13-revision-v1','','','2015-04-07 14:39:12','2015-04-07 13:39:12','',13,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/13-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(465,2,'2015-04-07 14:38:44','2015-04-07 13:38:44','<h2><a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-casestudy-e1426505179570.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-398\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-casestudy-e1426505179570.jpg\" alt=\"facilities HIPPO\" width=\"369\" height=\"549\" /></a>HIPPO Provide Waste Logistics Services to Retail and Office Fit-out Projects</h2>\r\nHIPPO offer an effective service for use during the refurbishment or fit-out stage of retail and office premises.\r\n\r\nUsing a HIPPOBAG allows you to segregate waste streams on site, making it easy for you to increase your recycling rates, in turn helping you to achieve your diversion from landfill objectives.\r\n<h2>Efficient</h2>\r\nHIPPOBAGs are a waste logistics solution without the space or time restrictions that you will encounter when either buying a skip or handling waste logistics yourself. With the efficiencies in time and space that are delivered by HIPPOWASTE, your workforce will be more productive and your business will save money.\r\n<h2>flexible</h2>\r\nHIPPO offer an affordable, flexible and instant waste solution that is both transportable and bespoke to your project. In addition, HIPPOBAGs allow you to carry out the work at a suitable time for you, rather than when you are able to hire a skip. This way you can take greater control of your waste logistics operation and avoid unnecessary hassle during your retail or office fit out project.\r\n<h2>3 different sizes</h2>\r\nHIPPO’s strong, non-bulky skip alternatives come in three different sizes, so you can match the size of the HIPPOBAG you purchase to the size of the project you are undertaking, meaning that you will never pay for more than you need and will save valuable space around your project.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/case-studies/retail-case-study/\">Read our retail and office fit-out case study here</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-office-fitout.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-389\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-office-fitout.jpg\" alt=\"retail and office fitout HIPPO\" width=\"1200\" height=\"558\" /></a>','Retail and Office Fit-out','','inherit','open','open','','13-revision-v1','','','2015-04-07 14:38:44','2015-04-07 13:38:44','',13,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/13-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(467,2,'2015-04-08 09:52:12','2015-04-08 08:52:12','<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/contruction-casestudy.jpg\"><img class=\"  alignright wp-image-400 size-full\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/contruction-casestudy.jpg\" alt=\"Construction Casestudy HIPPO\" width=\"615\" height=\"918\" /></a>Where working space is often at a premium, the HIPPOBAG provides an efficient and environmentally sound method of waste segregation and disposal. McLaren Construction recently used the HIPPOBAG to boost environmental performance whilst undertaking their first joint construction and fit-out of a John Lewis Partnership At Home store.\n\nHIPPOWASTE recommended using the MIDIBAG as the most flexible solution; the one cubic yard bags fit comfortably on a standard pallet, allowing easy movement around site using a fork lift or pallet truck. Flat-packed bags were delivered in bulk ready to be placed near the source of the waste, reducing costly double-handling and minimising Health and Safety risks.\n\nThe bags were then consolidated for regular collection, preventing waste build up on site which could have restricted the project\'s delivery programme. To support the on-site team, HIPPOWASTE delivered Toolbox Talks to promote best practice when it comes to positioning, filling and arranging collection of the bags.\n\nLocating HIPPOBAGs at the point of waste generation allowed McLaren to keep working areas tidy. By labelling the bags for each major waste stream, McLaren were able to fully segregate their material. This proactive approach meant HIPPOWASTE have reported that 97% of the waste collected was diverted from landfill and recycled.\n\n[quote]\n<h3>What They Said About HIPPOWASTE</h3>\n<em>\"Working in partnership with HIPPOWASTE on this project was the ideal solution. The MIDIBAGS allowed us to keep the site tidy, whilst segregating the waste before collection boosted our recycling rates resulting in 97% diversion from landfill.\"</em>\n\nLeigh Steele, Fit-out Manager, McLaren Construction\n\n[/quote]','Interior Fit-Out with John Lewis and McLaren Construction','','inherit','open','open','','31-autosave-v1','','','2015-04-08 09:52:12','2015-04-08 08:52:12','',31,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/31-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(468,2,'2015-04-07 14:48:06','2015-04-07 13:48:06','<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-casestudy-e1426505179570.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-398\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-casestudy-e1426505179570.jpg\" alt=\"construction HIPPO\" width=\"400\" height=\"596\" /></a>HIPPOWASTE was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAt over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors, making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source.\r\n\r\nThe bags could then be easily manoeuvred to the ground floor, where they were placed for collection with no need to double handle the waste into another container.\r\n\r\n[quote]\r\n<h3>What they Said About HIPPOWASTE</h3>\r\n<em>\"The different sized HIPPOBAGs are ideal for the various waste streams generated on site and to date the flexibility and versatility afforded by this solution has enabled us to achieve 97% recycling in our first month on site. The friendly and efficient service from HIPPO complements and supports the effort inputted by the site team.\" </em>\r\n\r\nAndy Cartwright, Site Manager, Wates Retail\r\n\r\n[/quote]','Construction with Wates Retail and John Lewis','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2015-04-07 14:48:06','2015-04-07 13:48:06','',32,'http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/blog/32-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(469,2,'2015-04-07 14:48:25','2015-04-07 13:48:25','<a href=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-casestudy-e1426505179570.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-398\" src=\"http://hippo.tailoreddev.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/retail-casestudy-e1426505179570.jpg\" alt=\"construction HIPPO\" width=\"300\" height=\"447\" /></a>HIPPOWASTE was awarded the waste management contract by Wates Retail for the construction of Europe’s largest John Lewis department store in Liverpool. The new 240,000 square foot, multi-million pound John Lewis store is part of The Paradise Project – a regeneration project covering 42 acres in the heart of the city.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAt over five storeys high, this complex construction development required a flexible, easily transportable waste removal solution. Using HIPPOBAGs enabled Wates to set up waste segregation on each of the four sales floors, making it easy for the site teams to separate the waste at source.\r\n\r\nThe bags could then be 